1
00:01:07,000 --> 00:01:09,000
Belê temaşevanên hêja,
 
Yes, dear viewers,

2
00:01:09,000 --> 00:01:13,000
Vê carê jî em ê derbasî gundê Çolaqa bibin.
 
This time we will go to the village of Çolaqa.

3
00:01:13,000 --> 00:01:16,000
Gundê Çolaqa bi navçeya Cindirêsê ye.
 
The village of Çolaqa is in the Jindires district.

4
00:01:16,000 --> 00:01:19,000
Roja cejnê em derbasî gundê Çolaqa bibin.
 
On the day of the Eid, we will go to the village of Çolaqa.

5
00:01:19,000 --> 00:01:22,000
Inikî, urf û edetê cejnê em nas bikin.
 
To get to know the customs and traditions of the Eid now.

6
00:01:22,000 --> 00:01:26,000
Berî gundê Çolaqa çawa jiyana xwe derbas dikir, niha çawa
derbas dikin,
 
How the village of Çolaqa lived before, how they live now,

7
00:01:26,000 --> 00:01:29,000
Ê ro ka amadekariyên gundê Çolaqa çi hazir kirine,
 
And what preparations the village of Çolaqa has made today,

8
00:01:29,000 --> 00:01:49,000
Em ê bi hev re derbas bibin, em ê bi hev re nas bikin.
 
We will go together, and get to know them together.

9
00:02:38,000 --> 00:02:40,000
Birêz Mihemed merhaba ji we re.
 
Mr. Mohammed, hello to you.

10
00:02:40,000 --> 00:02:41,000
Merhaba ji te re jî.
 
Hello to you too.

11
00:02:41,000 --> 00:02:42,000
Cejna we pîroz be.
 
Happy Eid.

12
00:02:42,000 --> 00:02:44,000
Ya te jî pîroz be.
 
Happy Eid to you too.

13
00:02:44,000 --> 00:02:47,000
Me xwest di roja cejnê de em derbasî cem we bibin,
 
We wanted to come to you on the day of the Eid,

14
00:02:47,000 --> 00:02:50,000
Inikî em gundê Çolaqa nas bikin.
 
So that we can get to know the village of Çolaqa now.

15
00:02:50,000 --> 00:02:53,000
Em me xwest destpêkê da navê gund ji ku hatiye, navê Çolaq?
 
We wanted to start with where the name of the village came
from, the name Çolaq?

16
00:02:53,000 --> 00:02:56,000
Mezinên me jî ji me re digotin dibêjin bi navê yekî,
 
Our elders also used to tell us, they say it was named after
someone,

17
00:02:56,000 --> 00:02:58,000
Destê wî çolak bû, bi nav lê kirine Çolaq.
 
His hand was crippled, so they named it Çolaq.

18
00:02:58,000 --> 00:02:59,000
Yenê gund bi navê wî hatiye naskirin?
 
So the village was named after him?

19
00:02:59,000 --> 00:03:00,000
Erê.
 
Yes.

20
00:03:00,000 --> 00:03:01,000
Ê berê gundî we li ku derê bûn?
 
And where was your village before?

21
00:03:01,000 --> 00:03:04,000
Berê ev gundna li çiya bûn.
 
Before, these villages were in the mountains.

22
00:03:04,000 --> 00:03:05,000
Li çiya bûn.
 
They were in the mountains.

23
00:03:05,000 --> 00:03:06,000
Ev çiyana jî,
 
These mountains,

24
00:03:06,000 --> 00:03:09,000
Gir hember hev din e, gir û hurç bûn.
 
They are hills opposite each other, they were rough hills.

25
00:03:09,000 --> 00:03:10,000
Her malbatek,
 
Every family,

26
00:03:10,000 --> 00:03:11,000
Malbatek di şkeftên xwe da,
 
Lived in their own caves,

27
00:03:11,000 --> 00:03:13,000
Jiyan dikirin.
 
They lived.

28
00:03:13,000 --> 00:03:14,000
Pezê xwe hebûn.
 
They had their sheep.

29
00:03:14,000 --> 00:03:17,000
Heyatî koçberî bûn.
 
They lived a nomadic life.

30
00:03:17,000 --> 00:03:19,000
Li wê derê, mezin dibûn.
 
In that place, they grew up.

31
00:03:19,000 --> 00:03:22,000
Ji ber wê derketin.
 
From there, they came out.

32
00:03:22,000 --> 00:03:24,000
Vê derê.
 
To here.

33
00:03:24,000 --> 00:03:25,000
Ê li ku derê, ew şkeftna li ku derê ne?
 
And where, where are those caves?

34
00:03:25,000 --> 00:03:28,000
Ew şkeftna li Şemalî gund in.
 
Those caves are north of the village.

35
00:03:28,000 --> 00:03:29,000
Ji vê derê nêzîk in yan dûr in?
 
Are they close or far from here?

36
00:03:29,000 --> 00:03:30,000
Nêzîk in, na na.
 
They are close, no no.

37
00:03:30,000 --> 00:03:34,000
Deh pênzdeh deqîqe tu peyagî.
 
You can get there in ten to fifteen minutes on foot.

38
00:03:34,000 --> 00:03:36,000
Yenê kîlometrek heye?
 
So, is it a kilometer?

39
00:03:36,000 --> 00:03:39,000
Kîlometrek heye.
 
It's about a kilometer.

40
00:03:39,000 --> 00:03:40,000
Ê çiqas şkeft li wê derê hene?
 
And how many caves are there?

41
00:03:40,000 --> 00:03:43,000
Welah çar-pênc şkeft li wê derê ne.
 
By God, there are four or five caves there.

42
00:03:43,000 --> 00:03:44,000
Çar şkeft hene.
 
There are four caves.

43
00:03:44,000 --> 00:03:48,000
Ê ew malbatên ku li wê derê jiyan dikirin, ev şkeftna di kî
bûn?
 
And those families that lived there, whose caves were they?

44
00:03:48,000 --> 00:03:51,000
Ew malbatna wê derê, ew malbatna ku ez dibêjim,
 
Those families there, the families that I am talking about,

45
00:03:51,000 --> 00:03:54,000
Ew e, malbat ku ew der asas girtibûn.
 
It is them, the family that established the foundation of
this place.

46
00:03:54,000 --> 00:03:56,000
Evder malê Baskê yek jê,
 
The family of Baskê is one of them,

47
00:03:56,000 --> 00:03:57,000
Bi navê Çolaq tê naskirin.
 
It is known by the name Çolaq.

48
00:03:57,000 --> 00:03:58,000
Malê Seydo hebûn.
 
The family of Seydo was there.

49
00:03:58,000 --> 00:03:59,000
Malê Bago hebûn.
 
The family of Bago was there.

50
00:03:59,000 --> 00:03:59,000
Malê Zîn Elîş jî hebûn.
 
The family of Rihanê was there.

51
00:03:59,000 --> 00:04:01,000
Malê Zîn Elîş jî hebûn.
 
The family of Zîn Elîş was also there.

52
00:04:01,000 --> 00:04:03,000
Berî ev na li wir bûn paşî derketin,
 
Before, these ones were there, and then they came out,

53
00:04:03,000 --> 00:04:04,000
Av li vê derê dîtin,
 
They found water here,

54
00:04:04,000 --> 00:04:05,000
Derbasî vê derê bûn.
 
They moved here.

55
00:04:05,000 --> 00:04:05,000
Û gund bi hêdî hêdî mezin bû.
 
Okay.

56
00:04:05,000 --> 00:04:08,000
Û gund bi hêdî hêdî mezin bû.
 
And the village gradually grew.

57
00:04:08,000 --> 00:04:10,000
Ê niha gund çiqas mal e?
 
And now, how many houses are in the village?

58
00:04:10,000 --> 00:04:11,000
Heştê mal heye.
 
There are eighty houses.

59
00:04:11,000 --> 00:04:13,000
Yenê gundê we, heştê mal e gundekî mezin e jî yenê.
 
So your village has eighty houses, it's a big village.

60
00:04:13,000 --> 00:04:16,000
Gundekî mezin e, heştê mal heye.
 
It is a big village, it has eighty houses.

61
00:04:16,000 --> 00:04:19,000
Û hejmara gundiyan jî millet tê de heye,
 
And the number of villagers, the people in it,

62
00:04:19,000 --> 00:04:21,000
Der dorî heft sed meriv heye.
 
There are about seven hundred people.

63
00:04:21,000 --> 00:04:22,000
Heft sed kes.
 
Seven hundred people.

64
00:04:22,000 --> 00:04:24,000
Ê gundê we jî gelek xweş e yenê,
 
And your village is very beautiful.

65
00:04:24,000 --> 00:04:28,000
Ev darên vir, ev xwezahiya vir gelek xweş e.
 
These trees here... this nature here is very beautiful.

66
00:04:28,000 --> 00:04:30,000
Xwezahiya gundê we gelek xweş e yenê.
 
The nature of your village is very beautiful.

67
00:04:30,000 --> 00:04:31,000
Rast e.
 
It's true.

68
00:04:31,000 --> 00:04:33,000
Biraderê delal,
 
Dear brother,

69
00:04:33,000 --> 00:04:37,000
Gundê me gundekî çandinî ye.
 
Our village is an agricultural village.

70
00:04:37,000 --> 00:04:40,000
Gundekî, tê de jiyana xwe xweş e.
 
A village where life is pleasant.

71
00:04:40,000 --> 00:04:43,000
Dewarên xwe jî pezê xwe, yê me di nav de warên pez jî heye.
 
We have our cattle... our sheep, we have places for sheep in
it.

72
00:04:43,000 --> 00:04:45,000
Bi cotkariya xwe tê naskirin.
 
It is known for its farming.

73
00:04:45,000 --> 00:04:46,000
Rêçberê xwe hebûn.
 
It had its farmers.

74
00:04:46,000 --> 00:04:49,000
Bav û kalên me, îş te, belê bûn evna,
 
Our ancestors, yes, they were... these ones,

75
00:04:49,000 --> 00:04:52,000
Rehmetî mamo hebû,
 
The late uncle was there,

76
00:04:52,000 --> 00:04:53,000
Kalikên me hebûn,
 
Our grandfathers were there,

77
00:04:53,000 --> 00:04:55,000
Yenê însanên me yî kevne-dar hebûn.
 
So, we had our old people.

78
00:04:55,000 --> 00:04:57,000
Ji te re, sibe zû dikişiyan ser dewarên xwe.
 
I tell you, early in the morning they would go to their
cattle.

79
00:04:57,000 --> 00:04:58,000
Cotê xwe dajotin.
 
They would plow their fields.

80
00:04:58,000 --> 00:05:01,000
Wekî xetê traktorê niha kako di dajotin lê dixistin.
 
Just like the line of a tractor today, brother, they would
plow and strike.

81
00:05:01,000 --> 00:05:04,000
Ev însan jî, d'icî de navdar bûn, nas kirin da bûn.
 
These people were famous in their place, they were known.

82
00:05:04,000 --> 00:05:06,000
Ê mezinên wê kî bûn berê?
 
And who were its elders before?

83
00:05:06,000 --> 00:05:11,000
Di her gundekî de ode, mîvanxane hene, rûspîyên wan hene.
 
In every village there are guest rooms, and they have their
elders.

84
00:05:11,000 --> 00:05:13,000
Odeyên mîvana,
 
The guest rooms...

85
00:05:13,000 --> 00:05:14,000
Ez bi xwe negihiştimê.
 
I myself didn't catch that time.

86
00:05:14,000 --> 00:05:15,000
Bavkên me ji me re heval dan.
 
Our fathers told us.

87
00:05:15,000 --> 00:05:16,000
Kalikên me ji me re heval dan.
 
Our grandfathers told us.

88
00:05:16,000 --> 00:05:18,000
Malê Eẍa hebû, Aẍayê mezin hebû.
 
The family of Agha was there, the big Agha was there.

89
00:05:18,000 --> 00:05:22,000
Û ew a odeyên mîvana malê Eẍa mezin evan,
 
And those guest rooms of the big Agha family... these ones,

90
00:05:22,000 --> 00:05:23,000
Çêkiribû.
 
They had built it.

91
00:05:23,000 --> 00:05:26,000
Lê dema feqîra jî di nav xwedî pirsgirêka çareser dikirin.
 
Even when the poor had problems among themselves, they would
solve them.

92
00:05:26,000 --> 00:05:28,000
Ji ber ku ev gunda, di wê demê gundê oxlera bû.
 
Because this village, at that time, was a village of aghas.

93
00:05:28,000 --> 00:05:30,000
Aẍlera li vê derê, vî gundî hukm dikir.
 
Aghas ruled here in this village.

94
00:05:30,000 --> 00:05:31,000
Feqîr jî hebûn.
 
There were poor people too.

95
00:05:31,000 --> 00:05:32,000
Li,
 
There...

96
00:05:32,000 --> 00:05:34,000
Silêmanê Koçer hebû.
 
Sleman Kocher was there.

97
00:05:34,000 --> 00:05:36,000
Rûspiyê me bû.
 
He was our elder.

98
00:05:36,000 --> 00:05:37,000
Malo Çolêq hebûn.
 
The Çolaq family was there.

99
00:05:37,000 --> 00:05:39,000
Eẍa mezin jî hebû.
 
The big Agha was there too.

100
00:05:39,000 --> 00:05:41,000
Diçûn kêşeya xwe, dinav xwe de çareser dikirin.
 
They would solve their problems among themselves.

101
00:05:41,000 --> 00:05:43,000
Di odeyê de çareser dikirin.
 
They would solve them in the room.

102
00:05:43,000 --> 00:05:45,000
Yenê kêşe bi derve de rêje nedidan.
 
So, they didn't let the problem go outside.

103
00:05:45,000 --> 00:05:46,000
Bi derve derê rêje nedidan.
 
They didn't let it go outside.

104
00:05:46,000 --> 00:05:50,000
Û gihayî hev hez dikir, ev de îhtiram dikirin.
 
And everyone loved each other, they respected each other.

105
00:05:50,000 --> 00:05:54,000
Yenê, gundê me ji hezkirinê da, û ji xwebaziyê da, pir
gundekî dewlemend bû, zengîn bû yenê.
 
So, in terms of love and tolerance, our village was a very
rich village.

106
00:05:54,000 --> 00:05:56,000
Zengîn bû, pir xweş bû.
 
It was rich, it was very beautiful.

107
00:05:56,000 --> 00:05:58,000
Ê niha, Mihemed,
 
And now, Mohammed,

108
00:05:58,000 --> 00:05:59,000
Dema cejnan,
 
During the holidays,

109
00:05:59,000 --> 00:06:01,000
Di cejnê de em derbasî cem we bûn.
 
During the Eid, we came to you.

110
00:06:01,000 --> 00:06:04,000
Ê berê dema cejnê da, we çawa cejna xwe bi hev re pîroz
dikir?
 
And before, during the Eid, how did you celebrate your
holiday together?

111
00:06:04,000 --> 00:06:06,000
Em pê dihesîn, millet,
 
We would feel it, the people,

112
00:06:06,000 --> 00:06:07,000
Gî, xudî li hev derdiket.
 
Everyone looked after each other.

113
00:06:07,000 --> 00:06:09,000
Diçûn zîyaretî hev din dikirin.
 
They went and visited each other.

114
00:06:09,000 --> 00:06:11,000
Eyda xwe,
 
Their Eid,

115
00:06:11,000 --> 00:06:13,000
Ser edana hev dikirin.
 
They would congratulate each other.

116
00:06:13,000 --> 00:06:15,000
Xwarinê xwe bi hev re çêdikirin.
 
They would cook their food together.

117
00:06:15,000 --> 00:06:16,000
Xwarin bi hev ra dixwarin.
 
They would eat food together.

118
00:06:16,000 --> 00:06:19,000
Cejnê xwe bi hev re derbas dikirin.
 
They would spend their Eid together.

119
00:06:19,000 --> 00:06:22,000
Yenê, ew rojên wê, rojên pir xweş bûn.
 
So, those days, they were very beautiful days.

120
00:06:22,000 --> 00:06:25,000
Rojên pir xweş li ser me derbas dibûn.
 
Very beautiful days passed over us.

121
00:06:25,000 --> 00:06:28,000
Yenê, rast e ew rewş dîsa em pê nagîjin,
 
So, it is true that we didn't really catch those days,

122
00:06:28,000 --> 00:06:30,000
Lê belê me heval dan,
 
But they told us,

123
00:06:30,000 --> 00:06:31,000
Digot cejna me,
 
They said our Eid...

124
00:06:31,000 --> 00:06:33,000
Yenê, ew wexta pir wextekî xweş bû.
 
So, that time was a very beautiful time.

125
00:06:33,000 --> 00:06:35,000
Pir wextekî xweş bû. Ser me derbas dibû.
 
It was a very beautiful time. It passed over us.

126
00:06:35,000 --> 00:06:37,000
Yenê niha,
 
So now,

127
00:06:37,000 --> 00:06:38,000
Ferqa niha û wî çaxî da,
 
The difference between now and that time,

128
00:06:38,000 --> 00:06:40,000
Ferq cudayî pir tê heye.
 
There is a very big difference.

129
00:06:40,000 --> 00:06:43,000
Ê niha, dîsa hûn bi hev re xwarinê naxwin?
 
And now, don't you eat food together anymore?

130
00:06:43,000 --> 00:06:44,000
Xwarinê na, em naxwin.
 
Food, no, we don't eat it.

131
00:06:44,000 --> 00:06:46,000
Niha bû malbat.
 
Now it has become families.

132
00:06:46,000 --> 00:06:48,000
Bû malbat. Çima bû malbat?
 
It became families. Why did it become families?

133
00:06:48,000 --> 00:06:49,000
Berê ji malbat bûn.
 
Before, they were from the family.

134
00:06:49,000 --> 00:06:51,000
Niha,
 
Now,

135
00:06:51,000 --> 00:06:52,000
Ew feterê wê demê û niha,
 
Between that period of time and now,

136
00:06:52,000 --> 00:06:54,000
Ferq cuda tê heye.
 
There is a separate difference.

137
00:06:54,000 --> 00:06:56,000
Ew qonaxa ne wek qonaxa noke ye.
 
That era is not like the current era.

138
00:06:56,000 --> 00:06:58,000
Demê em di nav da, jiyan dikin,
 
The time we live in,

139
00:06:58,000 --> 00:06:59,000
Yenê gelkî û adetî derketin?
 
So the traditions and customs have faded?

140
00:06:59,000 --> 00:07:01,000
Eywa. Adet û teqalîd dûr ketin.
 
Yes. The customs and traditions have faded away.

141
00:07:01,000 --> 00:07:02,000
Dûr ketin.
 
They faded away.

142
00:07:02,000 --> 00:07:03,000
Niha qusûrê me bi xwe heye.
 
Now the fault is our own.

143
00:07:03,000 --> 00:07:04,000
Niha ev jî ji me e, kurd in.
 
Now these are from us, we are Kurds.

144
00:07:04,000 --> 00:07:06,000
Gî merivê me kurd in.
 
All our people are Kurds.

145
00:07:06,000 --> 00:07:08,000
Çend merên me, rûspî niha bi şalwar mane.
 
How many of our men, elders, are left wearing baggy trousers
now?

146
00:07:08,000 --> 00:07:11,000
Çend merivê me jin niha bi fîstanê kirmancî mane.
 
How many of our women are left wearing Kurdish dresses now?

147
00:07:11,000 --> 00:07:14,000
Ev adet, urfên me nas nedikir, rabûn.
 
We didn't recognize these customs and traditions, they
disappeared.

148
00:07:14,000 --> 00:07:16,000
Niha, belkî berê me Mihemed tenkê,
 
Now, maybe before, Mohammed simply,

149
00:07:16,000 --> 00:07:18,000
Kincekî me yê kurdî nav da xwegirtî.
 
Wore one of our Kurdish clothes.

150
00:07:18,000 --> 00:07:19,000
Em ji wê îftîxar in.
 
We are proud of that.

151
00:07:19,000 --> 00:07:20,000
Ew jî di xwe kiriye.
 
He has worn it too.

152
00:07:20,000 --> 00:07:22,000
Qusûrê me bi xwe ye. Me şaş kir.
 
The fault is our own. We made a mistake.

153
00:07:22,000 --> 00:07:24,000
Ev urf û edetê me kevin,
 
These old customs and traditions of ours,

154
00:07:24,000 --> 00:07:25,000
Me jinan re radibûn.
 
We women, they have stood up.

155
00:07:25,000 --> 00:07:26,000
Fikr, em dixwazin,
 
Thought, we want,

156
00:07:26,000 --> 00:07:27,000
Niha tak ra em vegerin.
 
Now we definitely want to return.

157
00:07:27,000 --> 00:07:28,000
Urf û adetê xwe ê kevin.
 
To our old customs and traditions.

158
00:07:28,000 --> 00:07:29,000
Em vegerin.
 
Let's return.

159
00:07:29,000 --> 00:07:33,000
Cejna me yê berê, ji ser me derbas bibû, yê hezkirinê ma hîn
di nav da be,
 
Our past Eid that passed over us, that love should still be
among us,

160
00:07:33,000 --> 00:07:35,000
Û hîn hîn em
 
And still, still we,

161
00:07:35,000 --> 00:07:38,000
Em şahî ji me da, ji me re xweş be em bibînin.
 
For a celebration from us, for it to be pleasant for us to
see.

162
00:07:38,000 --> 00:07:39,000
Yenê,
 
So,

163
00:07:39,000 --> 00:07:40,000
Hêviya te ew e,
 
Your hope is that,

164
00:07:40,000 --> 00:07:42,000
Hêviya her miletekî,
 
The hope of every nation,

165
00:07:42,000 --> 00:07:43,000
Dixwaze jin da vegere,
 
Is to return to it again,

166
00:07:43,000 --> 00:07:45,000
Ew tiştê bav û kalan da mayî.
 
Those things left by the ancestors.

167
00:07:45,000 --> 00:07:46,000
Em hîn e li ser rêça wan bimeşin.
 
To still... walk on their path.

168
00:07:46,000 --> 00:07:48,000
Erê, ku ev der heye.
 
Yes, that this place exists.

169
00:07:48,000 --> 00:07:50,000
L'dor bavê xwe, di berê xwe,
 
Around their fathers, before them,

170
00:07:50,000 --> 00:07:52,000
Civînan, xwarinê xwe bi hev re çêbikin, di xwarin.
 
Gatherings, cooking their food together, eating.

171
00:07:52,000 --> 00:07:54,000
Darin pismamê, apê xwe.
 
The cousins, the uncles.

172
00:07:54,000 --> 00:07:56,000
Di cem birayê xwe, xwarinê wan,
 
With their brothers, their food...

173
00:07:56,000 --> 00:07:58,000
Mirovên xwe, eydî xwe bi hev re de kin.
 
Their relatives, celebrating their Eid together.

174
00:07:58,000 --> 00:07:59,000
Dîsa, gundê me.
 
Again, our village.

175
00:07:59,000 --> 00:08:00,000
Ger mirîye a re ye,
 
If there is a death,

176
00:08:00,000 --> 00:08:01,000
Ger dewet a re ye,
 
If there is a wedding,

177
00:08:01,000 --> 00:08:02,000
Ger şahîy a re ye, ji ferah a re ye,
 
If there is a celebration, for joy,

178
00:08:02,000 --> 00:08:03,000
Gî tifaqîya milet,
 
All the unity of the people,

179
00:08:03,000 --> 00:08:05,000
Bi hev ra muşereke dikin.
 
They participate together.

180
00:08:05,000 --> 00:08:07,000
Xwedî li hev derdikevin.
 
They take care of each other.

181
00:08:07,000 --> 00:08:08,000
Yenê nîmeteke pir mezin e.
 
This is a very great blessing.

182
00:08:08,000 --> 00:08:11,000
Her weha niha gava em man e,
 
Just as we have stayed now,

183
00:08:11,000 --> 00:08:12,000
Li ser erdê bi,
 
On the land with...

184
00:08:12,000 --> 00:08:14,000
Bi rêberiya me, hevalên me,
 
With the guidance of us, our friends,

185
00:08:14,000 --> 00:08:15,000
Yek peke, yek pece.
 
YPG, YPJ.

186
00:08:15,000 --> 00:08:16,000
Asayîş, tevdema.
 
Asayish, Tev-Dem.

187
00:08:16,000 --> 00:08:18,000
Ev hevalên me niha, gava heta niha gava em diştin e,
 
These friends of ours now, until now when they left us,

188
00:08:18,000 --> 00:08:20,000
Bi van hîzan ser vî ardî mayî,
 
With these forces staying on this land,

189
00:08:20,000 --> 00:08:21,000
Tifaqîya milet,
 
The unity of the people,

190
00:08:21,000 --> 00:08:23,000
Hingî dunyayê di rûyê sûriyê gihi,
 
While the world across Syria altogether,

191
00:08:23,000 --> 00:08:24,000
Perîşan bû.
 
Was miserable.

192
00:08:24,000 --> 00:08:26,000
Me gava em li ser axa xwe man,
 
When we stayed on our land,

193
00:08:26,000 --> 00:08:29,000
Deka em ji axa xwe da jîyan man, em ji axa xwe dûr neketin.
 
When we stayed living on our land, we did not leave our
land.

194
00:08:29,000 --> 00:08:32,000
Niha gundê we, çi qas mal e? Çi qas mal tê de hene?
 
Now, how many houses are in your village? How many houses
are in it?

195
00:08:32,000 --> 00:08:35,000
Gundê me çi qas mal tê hene,
 
How many houses are in our village,

196
00:08:35,000 --> 00:08:37,000
Wek heştê malî,
 
About eighty houses,

197
00:08:37,000 --> 00:08:38,000
Tê heye.
 
Are in it.

198
00:08:38,000 --> 00:08:41,000
Milet ji gund derketiye? Ji gund derketine?
 
Have the people left the village? Did they leave the
village?

199
00:08:41,000 --> 00:08:42,000
Ji gund derketine.
 
They left the village.

200
00:08:42,000 --> 00:08:43,000
Çûne kuderê?
 
Where did they go?

201
00:08:43,000 --> 00:08:44,000
Ji gund derketine.
 
They left the village.

202
00:08:44,000 --> 00:08:46,000
Hinek malbat,
 
Some families,

203
00:08:46,000 --> 00:08:47,000
Ji gund derketine. Çûne.
 
Left the village. They went.

204
00:08:47,000 --> 00:08:49,000
Bixayiloxeya me yi mezin ra çûn,
 
A large part of our families left,

205
00:08:49,000 --> 00:08:52,000
Jiyana xwe ji nav milkê xwe de li Cindirêsê girtin.
 
They built their lives on their own property in Jindires.

206
00:08:52,000 --> 00:08:53,000
Li Cindirêsê girtin.
 
They built it in Jindires.

207
00:08:53,000 --> 00:08:55,000
Li Miskê girtin.
 
They built it in Miske.

208
00:08:55,000 --> 00:08:58,000
Li Ber Şêx Ebdulrehman, wer bên Kengirê.
 
In Ber Sheikh Abdulrahman, around Kangirê.

209
00:08:58,000 --> 00:08:59,000
Li wir jî girtin.
 
They built it there too.

210
00:08:59,000 --> 00:09:00,000
Li Qîlê girtin.
 
They built it in Qîlê.

211
00:09:00,000 --> 00:09:01,000
Li,
 
In...

212
00:09:01,000 --> 00:09:03,000
Birc Ebdalo.
 
Birc Ebdalo.

213
00:09:03,000 --> 00:09:05,000
Li Birc Ebdalo jî,
 
In Birc Ebdalo too,

214
00:09:05,000 --> 00:09:07,000
Li wir jî malbatan me hebûn Çolaqo.
 
We had our Çolaq families there too.

215
00:09:07,000 --> 00:09:10,000
Çûne li wir jî jiyana xwe kirin.
 
They went and lived their lives there too.

216
00:09:10,000 --> 00:09:15,000
Yenê di pênc gundan e? Miletê we ji vir di pênc gundan
derketiye?
 
So in five villages? Your people from here have left to five
villages?

217
00:09:15,000 --> 00:09:17,000
Çûne van pênc gundanan a.
 
They went to these five villages.

218
00:09:17,000 --> 00:09:19,000
Ê niha, kêşe gunda giştî gundê we?
 
And now, are all those villages from your village?

219
00:09:19,000 --> 00:09:20,000
Miletê we ye?
 
Are they your people?

220
00:09:20,000 --> 00:09:22,000
Şêx Ebdulrehman wer bên Kengirê.
 
Sheikh Abdulrahman around Kangirê.

221
00:09:22,000 --> 00:09:23,000
Ew hemî jî ji we ne?
 
Are all of them from you too?

222
00:09:23,000 --> 00:09:26,000
Ha. Malbatek tenê jî jê nîne. Ew jî,
 
Yes. There is only one family that is not. That too...

223
00:09:26,000 --> 00:09:27,000
Bojqî ye.
 
Is Boşqî.

224
00:09:27,000 --> 00:09:30,000
Birêz Mihemed niha di gundê we de çend malbat hene?
 
Mr. Mohammed, how many families are there in your village
now?

225
00:09:30,000 --> 00:09:33,000
Ew, yek malbat hene.
 
Well, there is only one family.

226
00:09:33,000 --> 00:09:35,000
Kê di kîjan e ji me re navê wan bêje.
 
Who are they? Tell us their names.

227
00:09:35,000 --> 00:09:36,000
Ez ji te re bêjim.
 
I will tell you.

228
00:09:36,000 --> 00:09:37,000
Wela Şerîf.
 
By God, Sharif.

229
00:09:37,000 --> 00:09:40,000
Malbatên di asasî ya vî gundî jiyan dikirin.
 
The families that basically lived in this village.

230
00:09:40,000 --> 00:09:42,000
Ê dihat naskirin,
 
That were known,

231
00:09:42,000 --> 00:09:44,000
Mala Axê bû.
 
It was the Agha family.

232
00:09:44,000 --> 00:09:47,000
Û mala Çolaq der dketin, Û mala Çolaq li vêrê digotin, Mala
Baskê.
 
And the Çolaq family came out, and the Çolaq family here,
they called it the Baskê family.

233
00:09:47,000 --> 00:09:48,000
Û mala Bago bûn.
 
And it was the Bago family.

234
00:09:48,000 --> 00:09:50,000
Piştî dema ku,
 
After the time when...

235
00:09:50,000 --> 00:09:52,000
Av li vir jiyan dibe,
 
Water brings life here,

236
00:09:52,000 --> 00:09:54,000
Der dikeve, li vê derê.
 
It appears, here.

237
00:09:54,000 --> 00:09:57,000
Di wê cîgaha, niha em tê de,
 
In this place, where we are now,

238
00:09:57,000 --> 00:09:58,000
Rûniştin e.
 
Sitting.

239
00:09:58,000 --> 00:10:00,000
Em eyda xwe lê dikin.
 
We are celebrating our Eid.

240
00:10:00,000 --> 00:10:06,000
Rûdibê, ew malbatna jî, gund da dikevin, vê çiyayî.
 
He said, those families also, they enter the village, in
this mountain.

241
00:10:06,000 --> 00:10:11,000
Ev malbatna jî, ez karim navê malbatan bidim, kî bûn.
 
These families as well, I can give the names of the
families, who they were.

242
00:10:11,000 --> 00:10:15,000
Malbata, malê Rehanê bûn.
 
The family, they were the Rehan family.

243
00:10:15,000 --> 00:10:18,000
Malbatên malê Zênelîşê bûn.
 
Families of the Zênelîş family.

244
00:10:18,000 --> 00:10:19,000
Malê Koçera bûn.
 
They were the Koçer family.

245
00:10:19,000 --> 00:10:21,000
Malê Mihemedê Şêxê bûn.
 
They were the Mihemed Şêx family.

246
00:10:21,000 --> 00:10:23,000
Malê Hisên Terkî bûn.
 
They were the Hisên Terkî family.

247
00:10:23,000 --> 00:10:28,000
Malê Lehm bûn, malê Berazî bûn, Mîradê Nehsê bû,
 
They were the Lehm family, the Berazî family, it was Mîrad
Nehs,

248
00:10:28,000 --> 00:10:30,000
Malê Şêx Heyder bûn,
 
They were the Şêx Heyder family,

249
00:10:30,000 --> 00:10:33,000
Û malê Hisên Terkî min got, malê...
 
And the Hisên Terkî family I said, family of...

250
00:10:33,000 --> 00:10:36,000
Û hindik malbatên din hebûn, xwedî eşîrek bûn.
 
And there were a few other families, they were a tribe.

251
00:10:36,000 --> 00:10:42,000
Kirîv jî, gundê me hebûn. Jiber ku ev gund, gundê Axleran
bû, kirîvên gundî jî hebûn.
 
We also had godfathers in our village. Because this village
was a village of Aghas, there were godfathers in the village
too.

252
00:10:42,000 --> 00:10:43,000
Kirîv jî hebûn.
 
There were godfathers too.

253
00:10:43,000 --> 00:10:46,000
Mala te ava be, spas ji te ra.
 
Bless your house, thank you.

254
00:10:46,000 --> 00:11:06,000
Sax bî, ehlen we sehlen.
 
Stay healthy, welcome.

255
00:11:08,000 --> 00:11:14,000
Gundê Çolaqa, yek ji gundên navçeya Cindirêsê. Çarde
kîlometreyan li rojavayê bajarê Cindirêsê,
 
The village of Çolaqa is one of the villages of the Cindirês
district. It's located fourteen kilometers west of the city
of Cindirês,

256
00:11:14,000 --> 00:11:18,000
û şazde kîlometreyan li rojavayê bajarê Efrînê dikeve.
 
and sixteen kilometers west of the city of Afrin.

257
00:11:18,000 --> 00:11:23,000
Navê gundê Çolaqa, ji navê kesekî destxwar bi navê Ehmedê
Hemze yê Reşo hatiye,
 
The name of the village of Çolaqa comes from the name of a
paralyzed person named Ehmedê Hemze Reşo,

258
00:11:23,000 --> 00:11:27,000
û ew weke yekemîn kes li gund niştecih bûye.
 
and he was the first person to settle in the village.

259
00:11:27,000 --> 00:11:31,000
Berê, şêniyên gund li şikeftan da li paş gund li aliyê
rojava bûn.
 
In the past, the residents of the village lived in the caves
behind the village on the west side.

260
00:11:31,000 --> 00:11:36,000
Piştre jî, ber peydabûna avê, ango vedîtina Kaniya
Bîrkinikê,
 
Later, due to the appearance of water, meaning the discovery
of the Bîrkinik Spring,

261
00:11:36,000 --> 00:11:54,000
gel hatin li derdorê niştecih bûn û xaniyên xwe ava kirin.
 
people came and settled around it and built their houses.

262
00:11:54,000 --> 00:11:55,000
Merheba ji we ra.
 
Hello to you.

263
00:11:55,000 --> 00:11:56,000
Ehlen we sehlen, bi te delal.
 
Welcome, dear.

264
00:11:56,000 --> 00:11:57,000
Cejna we pîroz be.
 
Happy Eid.

265
00:11:57,000 --> 00:12:00,000
Pîroz be. Cejna we, bi hemî cemaetê, bi hemî milet... em
giştan...
 
Happy Eid. Your Eid, with the whole congregation, with all
the people... we all...

266
00:12:00,000 --> 00:12:02,000
pîroz dikin.
 
congratulate it.

267
00:12:02,000 --> 00:12:03,000
Em ê navê nas bikin destpêkê?
 
Shall we know your name first?

268
00:12:03,000 --> 00:12:04,000
Ebo Reşo.
 
Ebo Reşo.

269
00:12:04,000 --> 00:12:05,000
Wî li ser çavên min.
 
Upon my eyes.

270
00:12:05,000 --> 00:12:06,000
Çavên te sax bin.
 
May your eyes be healthy.

271
00:12:06,000 --> 00:12:07,000
Ebdurehman.
 
Ebdurehman.

272
00:12:07,000 --> 00:12:08,000
Li ser çavê min.
 
Upon my eye.

273
00:12:08,000 --> 00:12:09,000
Çavên te sax bin.
 
May your eyes be healthy.

274
00:12:09,000 --> 00:12:13,000
Apê Ebo, min xwest em dîroka gundê Çolaqa em nas bikin.
 
Uncle Ebo, I wanted us to get to know the history of the
village of Çolaqa.

275
00:12:13,000 --> 00:12:18,000
Ew behsa avê kirin, gotin berê gundê me li jor bû. Piştre
hatin av li vir dîtin.
 
They talked about water, they said our village was up there
in the past. Then they came and found water here.

276
00:12:18,000 --> 00:12:22,000
Û we jî behs kir wekû ava heye wekû kanî, piştre ava
çêkiriye.
 
And you also mentioned that there was water like a spring,
then they made the water.

277
00:12:22,000 --> 00:12:25,000
Wê kengî li vir çêkir? Ev bîra?
 
When did they make it here? This well?

278
00:12:25,000 --> 00:12:32,000
Havêl. Wextê şivan li jor diçêriya... pezê xwe diçêriya.
 
Friend. When the shepherd was grazing up there... grazing
his sheep.

279
00:12:32,000 --> 00:12:37,000
Wextê nêzîkî hev qetiyan, şivana no bîn e... Pez... pezê xwe
avê, nêrî... tenê.
 
When they got close to each other, the shepherds couldn't
see... The sheep... it saw the water... alone.

280
00:12:37,000 --> 00:12:44,000
Tê li vê derê, erd dize, dê taniya ku av vedixwe, wextê av
jê vedixwe, ewî xwe şil dibe.
 
It comes here, the earth leaks, from the part where it
drinks water, when it drinks water from it, it gets wet.

281
00:12:44,000 --> 00:12:49,000
Zivirî, tê pez, şivan balê xwe didiyê. Balê xwe didiyê
welleh,
 
It returns, the sheep comes, the shepherd looks at it. He
looks at it, by God,

282
00:12:49,000 --> 00:12:51,000
evê xwe şil bûn e. Dibê av li vir e.
 
it got itself wet. He says water is here.

283
00:12:51,000 --> 00:12:54,000
Ket pê, nêrî, miqarebe kirin, ev derê av derket.
 
He followed it, looked, they observed it, water came out
from here.

284
00:12:54,000 --> 00:13:00,000
Piştre dî dî malên Beko û malên Baskî, sê çar aîle gişt
hatin avê li vir bûn.
 
After that, the Beko family and the Baskî family, three or
four families in total came to the water here.

285
00:13:00,000 --> 00:13:04,000
Rû vir, gîk dibe bor...
 
Setting here, it becomes a pipe...

286
00:13:04,000 --> 00:13:08,000
Hatin li vê derê, pey ketin, ev şopa avê, avê.
 
They came here, followed this water trace, the water.

287
00:13:08,000 --> 00:13:14,000
Vê derê bar, hatin, gund girtin, gundê Çolaqa. Nav lê kirin
Çolaqa.
 
In this area they loaded, they came, they built the village,
the village of Çolaqa. They named it Çolaqa.

288
00:13:14,000 --> 00:13:18,000
Ser wê îspata avê, kulan av bû bahr maşallah.
 
On the evidence of that water, they dug it and the water
became a sea, Mashallah.

289
00:13:18,000 --> 00:13:22,000
Vê ava, çar deh gund dihatin ava me dibir, nerxê xwe tunebû.
 
This water, fourteen villages would come and take our water,
it had no price.

290
00:13:22,000 --> 00:13:30,000
Xirza, Aşka, Gewrika, Feqîra, gişt dihatin ava me bi dewaran
dikşandin nerxê xwe tunebû.
 
Xirza, Aşka, Gewrika, Feqîra, all of them would come and
draw our water with animals, it had no price.

291
00:13:30,000 --> 00:13:33,000
Yanî digotin bîra kinik. Bîrkinik.
 
Meaning they called it the short well. Bîrkinik.

292
00:13:33,000 --> 00:13:35,000
Bîrkinik. Nav lê kirin Bîrkinik.
 
Bîrkinik. They named it Bîrkinik.

293
00:13:35,000 --> 00:13:37,000
Avê gişt gund dihatin, ser bîr hezkirin.
 
The water, all the villages came, they loved the well.

294
00:13:37,000 --> 00:13:38,000
Ev berê kanî bû yanî?
 
So this was a spring before?

295
00:13:38,000 --> 00:13:39,000
Kanî bû. Erê wekî kaniyê bû.
 
It was a spring. Yes, it was like a spring.

296
00:13:39,000 --> 00:13:41,000
Û kê tenzîm kirin we çêkirin?
 
And who organized it and built it?

297
00:13:41,000 --> 00:13:43,000
Milet çêkir, gund çêkir.
 
The people built it, the village built it.

298
00:13:43,000 --> 00:13:45,000
Wekî vir kanî ye... lê neha ev bîr e.
 
If this here is a spring... but now this is a well.

299
00:13:45,000 --> 00:13:49,000
Wekû vir kanî bû. Milet gund çêkir.
 
It was like a spring here. The people built the village.

300
00:13:49,000 --> 00:13:55,000
Gund... gund li vir şên bû, aîle çêkirin, xwedan kêla...
aîle...
 
The village... the village prospered here, they formed
families, the owner of the tombstone... families...

301
00:13:55,000 --> 00:13:56,000
aîle pir bûn.
 
families became many.

302
00:13:56,000 --> 00:13:59,000
Lê çawa bîr çêkirin?
 
But how did they build the well?

303
00:13:59,000 --> 00:14:06,000
Çolaq mezin bû, mezin bû... yanî nîvê bar kirin Heleb, nîvê
bar kirin... Kankorê, tiştê ew a... kirin.
 
Çolaq grew, it grew... I mean, half of them moved to Aleppo,
half of them moved to... Kankorê, things like that... they
did.

304
00:14:06,000 --> 00:14:14,000
Va kirin bîrkinik, û hewzek li vê derê avê hebû. Hewzê
tebîreta makînayê, tebîra ku av tê re bû.
 
This one they made into Bîrkinik, and there was a pool of
water here. A pool of machinery expression, an expression
where the water comes through.

305
00:14:14,000 --> 00:14:15,000
Di vê geliyê da bû?
 
Was it in this valley?

306
00:14:15,000 --> 00:14:16,000
Erê hewzê wicî bû.
 
Yes, the pool was there.

307
00:14:16,000 --> 00:14:21,000
Yanî berê av dirêj bû, we dem av derçû... ev a kû girtin
çiq-çiq kirin, wekî bilind kirin?
 
I mean, before the water was long, when the water came
out... they took this and made it step-by-step, like they
raised it?

308
00:14:21,000 --> 00:14:28,000
Bilind kirin û şirik ji vê derê kor ko şirik kirin, çar
şirik kirin, ew av tê re berdidê.
 
They raised it and made a spout from this blind side, they
made four spouts, the water releases through them.

309
00:14:28,000 --> 00:14:32,000
Û hewza li vir hebû. Berê şên bû ser bîrê.
 
And there was a pool here. Previously, it prospered on the
well.

310
00:14:32,000 --> 00:14:33,000
Çima bilind kirin?
 
Why did they raise it?

311
00:14:33,000 --> 00:14:37,000
Ji bo lemişte. Me'nî lemişte, baran mola ne xetme.
 
Because of the flood. Meaning the flood, the rain wouldn't
clog it.

312
00:14:37,000 --> 00:14:40,000
Dema baran têt wî dema ew ro gelî ye. Ev ro lemişte gelî
pişk nake.
 
When the rain comes, that time it flows down the valley. So
the flood doesn't spray the valley today.

313
00:14:40,000 --> 00:14:44,000
Manê lemişte. Manê barana negere ser wê.
 
So it wouldn't flood. So the rain wouldn't go over it.

314
00:14:44,000 --> 00:14:45,000
Ji bo me'nî ranekirin.
 
Meaning they raised it for this reason.

315
00:14:45,000 --> 00:14:46,000
Erê.
 
Yes.

316
00:14:46,000 --> 00:14:47,000
Em tiştekî din jî bipirsin.
 
Let's ask something else too.

317
00:14:47,000 --> 00:14:50,000
Di gund de bîr hene, başqayî vê kaniyê?
 
Are there wells in the village, apart from this spring?

318
00:14:50,000 --> 00:14:56,000
Bîr hene li pişt gund hene di navbera gund de... ser
kaniyê... kaniyê, kaniyên bîra hene.
 
There are wells behind the village, there are some in the
middle of the village... on the spring... the spring, there
are spring wells.

319
00:14:56,000 --> 00:14:57,000
Çend bîr in? Qasî çend in?
 
How many wells? About how many?

320
00:14:57,000 --> 00:15:01,000
Welleh ev derê, yek heye, yek kevin in yanî.
 
By God, here, there is one, there's an old one, you see.

321
00:15:01,000 --> 00:15:04,000
Û kaniyên... dewra kevin de we dîsa du-sê kanî wisa hebûn?
 
And the springs... in the old times, you had two or three
springs like this again?

322
00:15:04,000 --> 00:15:05,000
Dewra du-sê bîr heye yanî, hebûn.
 
There are two or three wells in the area, they existed.

323
00:15:05,000 --> 00:15:07,000
Niha hîn av kaniyên hene?
 
Do you still have spring water now?

324
00:15:07,000 --> 00:15:11,000
Na, yek heye di zorê da û yek jî di koştî de, tune mî.
 
No, there is one in the tough terrain and one in the corner,
that's it.

325
00:15:11,000 --> 00:15:13,000
Êh niha hûn ava xwe ji ku derê tînin?
 
So now where do you bring your water from?

326
00:15:13,000 --> 00:15:16,000
Ava... ava... ji şîrketê ye.
 
Water... water... is from the company.

327
00:15:16,000 --> 00:15:18,000
Berî hemî milet dihatin ser vê.
 
Before, all the people used to come to this one.

328
00:15:18,000 --> 00:15:22,000
Berê şeş gunda av ji vir dibir. Bîra... av ji vir dihat
dibirin.
 
Before, six villages used to take water from here. The
well... water used to come from here and they took it.

329
00:15:22,000 --> 00:15:25,000
Ev darana kengî hatine çandin? Darên çinarê, ya darê tûyê...
 
When were these trees planted? The sycamore trees, or the
mulberry trees...

330
00:15:25,000 --> 00:15:30,000
Ev darana... çinar... digotin axayê mezin bavikê Xelîl
Axa...
 
These trees... the sycamore... they said the great Agha, the
father of Xelîl Axa...

331
00:15:30,000 --> 00:15:31,000
Mihemedê Se'îd Axa ev a çand.
 
Mihemed Se'îd Axa planted this.

332
00:15:31,000 --> 00:15:36,000
Hîn xwediyê odê ye, odeyê wî jî hîn ta niha ew a ku heye.
Hîn şirata wî ye.
 
He is still the owner of the guest room, his guest room is
still there until now. It's still his trace.

333
00:15:36,000 --> 00:15:43,000
Pelekî... hukûmet wek mîvanek bû di ba wî, cemaet pêr e peya
dibû. Wê da dixwar bûn derdixwar.
 
Once... the government was like a guest with him, the crowd
would get off by him. They ate there, they fed them there.

334
00:15:43,000 --> 00:15:45,000
Wî, Mihemed Axa bavê Xelîl Axa, çand.
 
He, Mihemed Axa, the father of Xelîl Axa, planted it.

335
00:15:45,000 --> 00:15:46,000
Ev çiqas sal, ev dar e, diçe?
 
How many years does this tree go back?

336
00:15:46,000 --> 00:15:56,000
Nizanim... qedîm e. Sed û heftê, sed sê sed sal e bibe,
kevin e, bav û kalên me mirin û di gotin Xelîl çandiye.
 
I don't know... it's ancient. A hundred and seventy, a
hundred to three hundred years it might be, it's old, our
ancestors died and said Xelîl planted it.

337
00:15:56,000 --> 00:15:57,000
Mala we ava be.
 
Bless your house.

338
00:15:57,000 --> 00:15:58,000
Sax be. Ehlê û sehlen.
 
Stay healthy. Welcome.

339
00:15:58,000 --> 00:15:59,000
Spas.
 
Thank you.

340
00:15:59,000 --> 00:16:19,000
Ser çava.
 
Upon my eyes.

341
00:16:24,000 --> 00:16:28,000
Nêzî heştê xanî û derdora heftsed kes li gund hene.
 
There are nearly eighty houses and around seven hundred
people in the village.

342
00:16:28,000 --> 00:16:32,000
Li rojavayê gund çiyayê Qerqînê û zeyaretek heye.
 
To the west of the village is Mount Qerqînê and there is a
shrine.

343
00:16:32,000 --> 00:16:34,000
Li başûr deşta Cûmê.
 
To the south is the Cûmê plain.

344
00:16:34,000 --> 00:16:40,000
Li başûr rojava çiyayê Kurk, li rojava çiyayê Simiqlî û
gundê Xirza.
 
To the southwest is Mount Kurk, to the west is Mount Simiqlî
and the village of Xirza.

345
00:16:40,000 --> 00:16:55,000
Û li bakur Xirabê Beko û Geliyê Heftêra.
 
And to the north are Xirabê Beko and the Heftêra Valley.

346
00:16:55,000 --> 00:17:00,000
Gundê Çolaqa bi pirbûna şikeftan navdar e. Lewma ta niha
gelek şikeft hene.
 
The village of Çolaqa is famous for its abundance of caves.
Therefore, there are still many caves.

347
00:17:00,000 --> 00:17:10,000
Mîna şikefta Xezalê, şikefta Elkurmî li bakurê gund, şikefta
Mamerî li başûr û şikefta Ketî li rojhilat e.
 
Such as the Xezalê cave, the Elkurmî cave to the north of
the village, the Mamerî cave to the south and the Ketî cave
to the east.

348
00:17:10,000 --> 00:17:17,000
Herwiha di her malekê de jî şikeftek heye û ta niha jî wekî
xwedîkirina sewalan û xwarina wan bi kar tînin.
 
In addition, every house has a cave, and even now they use
it for keeping animals and feeding them.

349
00:17:17,000 --> 00:17:35,000
Kaniya Şirkê û Bîra Jêrîn li bakur in, ku xelkê gund ava xwe
jê peyda dikin û pezên xwe jê av didin.
 
The Şirkê Spring and the Lower Well are in the north, where
the village people get their water and water their sheep.

350
00:17:35,000 --> 00:17:42,000
Dibistaneke seretayî ya kevnar li gund heye. Di sala 1951'an
de ava bû.
 
There is an ancient primary school in the village. It was
built in 1951.

351
00:17:42,000 --> 00:17:45,000
Û zarokên Çolaqa û gundên derdorê lê dixwendin.
 
And the children of Çolaqa and the surrounding villages
studied there.

352
00:17:45,000 --> 00:17:51,000
Mizgeftek û odeyeke, ku weke cihê kombûna gund bû, li gund
hene.
 
A mosque and a guest room, which was the village's gathering
place, exist in the village.

353
00:17:51,000 --> 00:17:56,000
Û du guvaşgehên kevnar yên zeytûnan jî li gund hebûn.
 
And two ancient olive presses were also present in the
village.

354
00:17:56,000 --> 00:18:03,000
Xelkê gund bi çandiniyê debara jiyana xwe dikin. Bi serî de
xwedîkirina zeviyên darên zeytûnan.
 
The village people make their living through agriculture.
Primarily the cultivation of olive tree fields.

355
00:18:03,000 --> 00:18:09,000
Di gel darên fêkî. Lê gel wan, gundî zeviyên bi dexil jî
diçînin.
 
Alongside fruit trees. But besides them, the villagers also
plant fields with grain.

356
00:18:09,000 --> 00:18:26,000
Di gel çandiniyê, hin malbat pez û çêlekên dihewinin û xwedî
dikin.
 
Along with agriculture, some families shelter and raise
sheep and cows.

357
00:18:26,000 --> 00:18:35,000
Mêrga sora siltanî... Nê mêrga sora siltanî...
 
The red meadow of the sultan... Oh the red meadow of the
sultan...

358
00:18:35,000 --> 00:18:42,000
Milor tehaw şedanî... bi milor tehaw şedanî...
 
You tied it with a string... you tied it with a string...

359
00:18:42,000 --> 00:18:48,000
Kuro bapê nizanî... ku xirî bapê nizanî...
 
Boy, your father didn't know... the boy, your father didn't
know...

360
00:18:48,000 --> 00:18:56,000
û xêmalê te helanî, û xêmalê te helanî...
 
and he lifted your trousseau, and he lifted your
trousseau...

361
00:18:56,000 --> 00:19:02,000
Reşo can, Reşo can... Mal a bavê Reşo...
 
Reşo dear, Reşo dear... The house of Reşo's father...

362
00:19:02,000 --> 00:19:08,000
Çar in çar in çar in çar in, periyên dika hîn aldar...
 
Four are, four are, four are, four are, the fairies of the
shop are still colorful...

363
00:19:08,000 --> 00:19:14,000
Lê Reşê, lê Reşê... Mal a bavê Reşo...
 
Oh Reşê, oh Reşê... The house of Reşo's father...

364
00:19:14,000 --> 00:19:20,000
Pênc in, pênc in, pênc in, pênc in, periya dika hîn li
gencan...
 
Five are, five are, five are, five are, the fairy of the
shop is still among the youth...

365
00:19:20,000 --> 00:19:26,000
Lê Reşê, lê Reşê... Mal a bavê Reşo...
 
Oh Reşê, oh Reşê... The house of Reşo's father...

366
00:19:26,000 --> 00:19:30,000
Çar in çar in çar in çar in, periya bi kîne hîn aldar...
 
Four are, four are, four are, four are, the fairies of the
shop are still colorful...

367
00:19:30,000 --> 00:19:35,000
Lê Reşê, lê Reşê... Mal a bavê Reşo na...
 
Oh Reşê, oh Reşê... The house of Reşo's father...

368
00:19:35,000 --> 00:19:42,000
Dayîka jî bi dilkî xweş, xastin dengekî xweş di şahiya xwe
de, cejnê da.
 
The mother also with a cheerful heart, they wanted a
beautiful voice in their celebration, during the Eid.

369
00:19:42,000 --> 00:19:46,000
Em ê başê destpêkê stranan ji me re gotin, dengê wan sax
bin.
 
Good that they sang songs for us at the beginning, may their
voices be healthy.

370
00:19:46,000 --> 00:19:56,000
Nah emê hinekî bipirsin ji wan da dema cejna de, dayîk çi
dikin, çawa bav û bira bi wan re alîkar in... dema
hazirtiyên xwe ji bo cejnê dikin.
 
Now we will ask them a bit about what mothers do during the
Eid, how fathers and brothers help them... when they make
their preparations for the Eid.

371
00:19:56,000 --> 00:19:58,000
Merheba ji we re dayê.
 
Hello to you, mother.

372
00:19:58,000 --> 00:20:00,000
Way... Ehlen we sehlen.
 
Oh... Welcome.

373
00:20:00,000 --> 00:20:04,000
Dayê ka ji destpêkê yanî cejnê...
 
Mother, from the beginning, I mean, Eid...

374
00:20:04,000 --> 00:20:08,000
Cejnê pêşînda em diçûn jêzara Xwarê, Kinc dikirîn
 
Before Eid, we used to go to Jêzara Xwarê and buy clothes.

375
00:20:08,000 --> 00:20:11,000
Em dihatin roja erefê... me haziriya xwe dikir
 
We would come back on the day of Arafah... we would make our
preparations.

376
00:20:11,000 --> 00:20:15,000
Kufteyê xwe dikir, nanê xwe rind dikir, bela dikir
 
We made our meatballs, we made our bread nicely and
distributed it.

377
00:20:15,000 --> 00:20:20,000
Me tiştê xwe gişt hazir dikir, be havâl cîranê xwe... em bi
me ra rûdiniştin, heta ku didan.
 
We prepared all our things, with our friends and
neighbors... we sat together until they were served.

378
00:20:20,000 --> 00:20:22,000
Em radibûn sibeha cejnê, sibeha cejnê jî em radibûn.
 
We would wake up on the morning of Eid.

379
00:20:22,000 --> 00:20:27,000
Dîsa nanê xwe dixwar, em bi cem hev diçûn cejna xwe pîroz
dikirn
 
We would eat our bread again, and we would go together to
celebrate our Eid.

380
00:20:27,000 --> 00:20:31,000
Hev ra hevalê xwe derdixistin em diçûna mala hevdû, ziyaretî
dikir.
 
We would take out our friends and go to each other's houses
and visit.

381
00:20:31,000 --> 00:20:33,000
Jê şûnda em diçûn, em eşxarê dilîstin.
 
Afterwards we would go, we would play games.

382
00:20:33,000 --> 00:20:37,000
Em alîstokê xwe... hinik çerxa betûşê dilîstin, hinik
qaşqelek didan.
 
With our toys... some played Ferris wheel, some played
seesaw.

383
00:20:37,000 --> 00:20:41,000
Ji wê, eşxê ra em nanê nîvro nedihat bîra em bixwin.
 
Out of the excitement of the game, we would forget to eat
lunch.

384
00:20:41,000 --> 00:20:45,000
Em difitilîn mala, nanê xwe çêdikir, êvarî dîsa em diçûn cem
hev
 
We would return home, make our food, and in the evening we
would go together again,

385
00:20:45,000 --> 00:20:46,000
Kêf dikirîn, giş şa dibûn.
 
We had fun, everyone was happy.

386
00:20:46,000 --> 00:20:50,000
Paşê em diçûna cem xudanê xwe. Em diçûn Eda Dûr e, em diçûn
gundê Bavê xwe.
 
Then we would go to our families. We would go to Eda Dûr, we
would go to our father's village.

387
00:20:50,000 --> 00:20:55,000
Xudanê xwe jî didîtan. Hava, ew me- yanê em di cejnê da bûn.
 
We would see our families too. Weather, that is, we were in
Eid.

388
00:20:55,000 --> 00:20:58,000
Ê rojekî kuftê tedar dibûn. Ser mîsan dibûn
 
One day meatballs would be ready. We would be at the tables.

389
00:20:58,000 --> 00:21:00,000
Tiştê wisa me da... dolme me çêdikir
 
Things like that... we made dolma.

390
00:21:00,000 --> 00:21:01,000
Yanî we şîv nan didan hev?
 
I mean, did you give food to each other?

391
00:21:01,000 --> 00:21:05,000
Erê, mêvanê me hatin em belavî nakin
 
Yes, when our guests arrived, we wouldn't let them leave.

392
00:21:05,000 --> 00:21:08,000
Lê ev qurbanê ha ew qurban heye, ewa goşt e, ewa cejna goşt
e, em datînan.
 
But this Eid al-Adha, there is sacrifice, that is meat, that
is the Eid of meat, we put it out.

393
00:21:08,000 --> 00:21:10,000
Îşta em ê mêvanê xwe...
 
Thus, our guests...

394
00:21:10,000 --> 00:21:17,000
Tişta herî xweş di gundan da çiye? Yanî dema ku dayîkê we bi
we re çêdikir...
 
What is the most beautiful thing in the villages? I mean
when your mother made it with you...

395
00:21:17,000 --> 00:21:23,000
Herî xweş nuha elhemdulîllah serok apo ji me ra fitilandiye
em dîsa jin û mêr gişt bi hev ra rûdinin.
 
The best thing now, Alhamdulillah, our leader Apo has
returned to us, and men and women all sit together again.

396
00:21:23,000 --> 00:21:25,000
Sîqetek di nava mirov da çêkir yanî.
 
He created a bond among the people.

397
00:21:25,000 --> 00:21:28,000
Dema ku dayîka te, cîranên te, çi kar dikirin?
 
When your mother, your neighbors, what work did they do?

398
00:21:28,000 --> 00:21:30,000
Te çi ji wan hîn dikir?
 
What did you learn from them?

399
00:21:30,000 --> 00:21:33,000
Pêşiya me... em pêşiya me, mesela, diwê em alîkariya xwe
nedikirin.
 
Before us... we, before us, for instance, they wouldn't help
us.

400
00:21:33,000 --> 00:21:36,000
Em ji me ra mesel dikir, em tevnek çêdikir.
 
They would explain things to us, we would weave a carpet.

401
00:21:36,000 --> 00:21:42,000
Bes me lê sêr dikir me jê radikir. Yanî wê çawa tevnek li
dar dikir û çawa çêdikir.
 
But we watched and learned from it. I mean, how they set up
the loom and how they made it.

402
00:21:42,000 --> 00:21:46,000
Me lê sêr dikir, bes me jê radikir. Me jê hez dikir em
karekî rind bibin.
 
We would watch, and we would learn. We loved it so we could
do good work.

403
00:21:46,000 --> 00:21:53,000
Bes me jê nedikirin, em diçûn... Qenewiç çêdikir, Şixlê
makînê hebû. Digotin Şixlê Teşrîfê, me çêdikir.
 
But we didn't do it, we went... They made cross-stitch,
there was machine embroidery. They called it Tashrif
embroidery, we made it.

404
00:21:53,000 --> 00:21:59,000
Ew em weha çêdikin, da qîza... Em pîr bûn em wisa çêdikin.
 
That's how we make it, so the girls... We got old, we make
it like that.

405
00:21:59,000 --> 00:22:01,000
Dayê ez tiştek ji te bipirsim?
 
Mother, can I ask you something?

406
00:22:01,000 --> 00:22:01,000
Di gundan da tiştê herî pir te xweş e ne?
 
Yes.

407
00:22:01,000 --> 00:22:05,000
Di gundan da tiştê herî pir te xweş e ne?
 
What are the most beautiful things in the villages?

408
00:22:05,000 --> 00:22:10,000
Dema cîran bi hev re tiştki dikin û alîkar, şîvê tînin...
 
When neighbors do something together and help each other,
they bring dinner...

409
00:22:10,000 --> 00:22:16,000
Çawa... Her malek xwarinek didin, şîvê li hev belav dikin.
Vêga ev edetê hene?
 
How... Each house gives food, they distribute dinner
together. Do these customs exist now?

410
00:22:16,000 --> 00:22:22,000
Em belav dikin evara eynî yek e. Her teqek xwarina xwe ez
şîvê dikim derdixînim
 
We distribute it, the evening is the same. Each puts out
their food, I make dinner and take it out.

411
00:22:22,000 --> 00:22:23,000
Yanî bi tenê xwe?
 
So by yourself?

412
00:22:23,000 --> 00:22:25,000
Ez tenê xwe didim, jina xwe didim jina bi hev didim.
 
I give by myself, I give to the women, we give to each
other.

413
00:22:25,000 --> 00:22:27,000
Hûn têne derve didine cîranan...
 
You bring it out and give it to the neighbors...

414
00:22:27,000 --> 00:22:30,000
Em cîrana jî didin, em bi cîranan didin, em diçên cîranan ne
nan...
 
We give it to the neighbors, we give it to the neighbors, we
go to the neighbors, not bread...

415
00:22:30,000 --> 00:22:32,000
Edetêk pir xweş e.
 
It's a very nice tradition.

416
00:22:32,000 --> 00:22:40,000
Erê. Noka yanî em... ev jî heye... ew jî tîne ji me ra ev jî
dibe ji wan ra yanî ev edeta di cem me da heye.
 
Yes. Now, I mean we... there is this too... they bring to us
and we bring to them, I mean we have this custom.

417
00:22:40,000 --> 00:22:44,000
Dema tu berê... te tiştin li ser zimên...
 
When you previously... you said some things about
language...

418
00:22:44,000 --> 00:22:49,000
Belkî ewên kesê temenên mezin, tiştê berê te bîra wan.
 
Maybe older people remember the old things.

419
00:22:49,000 --> 00:22:56,000
Belkî ev keçikên naha wisa tiştê berê nedînin, çawa te...
dema daîk û jinên li hev rûdiniştin.
 
Maybe these young girls nowadays haven't seen those old
things, how did you... when mothers and women used to sit
together.

420
00:22:56,000 --> 00:22:58,000
Çawa dibûn alîkar bi hev ra...
 
How they helped each other...

421
00:22:58,000 --> 00:23:11,000
Di her karê da em dibûn alîkar. Di nan da bû, didotina meşe
da bû, di mastê kevê da bû, di çêkirina penîr da bû.
 
We helped each other in every work. It was in bread making,
milking sheep, churning yogurt, making cheese.

422
00:23:11,000 --> 00:23:15,000
Û min dirûtin jî dikir, ha ev dirûyên me ne.
 
And I used to sew too, these are our clothes.

423
00:23:15,000 --> 00:23:17,000
Te bixwe terzî jî?
 
You were a tailor yourself?

424
00:23:17,000 --> 00:23:18,000
Çend sale dirûtinê dikî?
 
How many years have you been sewing?

425
00:23:18,000 --> 00:23:19,000
Hey vellah min pir kir.
 
Hey by God, I did a lot.

426
00:23:19,000 --> 00:23:20,000
Te pir kir?
 
You did a lot?

427
00:23:20,000 --> 00:23:23,000
Erê nuha qîzên min dibêje wer terzî
 
Yes, now my daughters say come become a tailor.

428
00:23:23,000 --> 00:23:25,000
Naha ez qey min 60-70 bûne terzî.
 
Now I must be 60-70, I have been a tailor.

429
00:23:25,000 --> 00:23:26,000
Xwedê te bihêle.
 
May God protect you.

430
00:23:26,000 --> 00:23:27,000
Te kî jê hîn kir?
 
Who taught you?

431
00:23:27,000 --> 00:23:29,000
Min destê diya xwe hîn kir.
 
I learned from my mother's hands.

432
00:23:29,000 --> 00:23:30,000
Te ji kê fêr kirî?
 
Who did you learn from?

433
00:23:30,000 --> 00:23:32,000
Ez ji kefenda... Ji kefendalê Jêrinim.
 
I am from Kefenda... From Lower Kefendal.

434
00:23:32,000 --> 00:23:34,000
Ji kefenda tu ne gundî çoloqaye?
 
From Kefenda, aren't you a villager of Çoloqaye?

435
00:23:34,000 --> 00:23:39,000
Nê...nê... ez Çoloqo me... ez mala bavê xwe ser ê deriyê.
Noka li vir xwe dikim
 
No... no... I am Çoloqo... I am from my father's house on
the door. Now I do it here.

436
00:23:39,000 --> 00:23:40,000
Dayê tu ji kû derê yî?
 
Mother, where are you from?

437
00:23:40,000 --> 00:23:41,000
Velleh ez qenterêm e.
 
By God, I am Qenterê.

438
00:23:41,000 --> 00:23:43,000
Gundê qenterê we li kîjan gundî nin?
 
Which village is your village of Qenterê in?

439
00:23:43,000 --> 00:23:44,000
Erê Qenterê me. Belê.
 
Yes, I am Qenterê. Yes.

440
00:23:44,000 --> 00:23:44,000
Ser çava wisa sax bin e, hala..
 
You are welcome.

441
00:23:44,000 --> 00:23:46,000
Ser çava wisa sax bin e, hala..
 
Thank you, be healthy, well..

442
00:23:46,000 --> 00:23:48,000
Sax bin.
 
Be healthy.

443
00:23:48,000 --> 00:23:52,000
Eme naha jî ji dayika vê min jî pirsin. Dayê!
 
Now we will ask this mother too. Mother!

444
00:23:52,000 --> 00:23:53,000
Destê we sax bin.
 
Bless your hands.

445
00:23:53,000 --> 00:23:57,000
Dayê! Naha me jî hazirtiya xwe konbê dikin?
 
Mother! Now we are also preparing our pastries?

446
00:23:57,000 --> 00:24:02,000
Me hinek çêkiriye, hinik jî niha rojek din Cejn e.
 
We have made some, and some will be for Eid another day.

447
00:24:02,000 --> 00:24:04,000
Kalek di gundê we da ser konbê da?
 
Does an old man in your village make pastries?

448
00:24:04,000 --> 00:24:05,000
Konbe?
 
Konbe?

449
00:24:05,000 --> 00:24:08,000
Ew çi çêdikin, çi têvedikin?
 
What do they make, what do they put in it?

450
00:24:08,000 --> 00:24:13,000
Welleh ar de, rûn e, şekir e.
 
By God, it is flour, oil, sugar.

451
00:24:13,000 --> 00:24:17,000
Kuncin e. Reş reşik in.
 
It's sesame seeds. It's black cumin.

452
00:24:17,000 --> 00:24:19,000
Mihleb e.
 
It is mahleb.

453
00:24:19,000 --> 00:24:24,000
Tiştên hawal dim... Ev tiştên ha em dikin.
 
Such things... We do these things.

454
00:24:24,000 --> 00:24:26,000
Û em mêze dikin. Çêdikin qaliban dixin.
 
And we look at it. We make it and put it in molds.

455
00:24:26,000 --> 00:24:28,000
Hûn tiştek din çi çêdikin?
 
What else do you make?

456
00:24:28,000 --> 00:24:30,000
Başqa em konba çêdikin, em xurîbe çêdikin,
 
Besides making konbe, we make qurabiya.

457
00:24:30,000 --> 00:24:33,000
Em qaqa çêdikin. Em mehmiro çêdikin.
 
We make qaq. We make maamoul.

458
00:24:33,000 --> 00:24:36,000
Hûn li berê çi dikirin... çend sal e evan dikin?
 
What did you do in the past... how many years have you been
making these?

459
00:24:36,000 --> 00:24:37,000
Em ji berê da dikin.
 
We've been making them since the past.

460
00:24:37,000 --> 00:24:38,000
Daykê we...
 
Your mothers...

461
00:24:38,000 --> 00:24:39,000
Dayikê me li pêş me çêdikirin
 
Our mothers used to make them before us.

462
00:24:39,000 --> 00:24:42,000
Berê kehrebe tîne bû, firne tîne bû.
 
Back then there was no electricity, no oven.

463
00:24:42,000 --> 00:24:47,000
Li ser êgir wisa niha, li ser êgir... me dikirin...
 
On the fire like this now, on the fire... we used to put...

464
00:24:47,000 --> 00:24:51,000
Sêle me didanîn. Me agir li ser çêdikir, me li binî agir
çêdikir.
 
We used to put the saac. We made fire on top, we made fire
underneath.

465
00:24:51,000 --> 00:24:52,000
Me konbê xwe dipiraştin.
 
We baked our pastries.

466
00:24:52,000 --> 00:24:55,000
Fatirok çû cîh, kehrebe hat.
 
When the oven came, electricity came.

467
00:24:55,000 --> 00:24:59,000
Danê pêş ket... Me bi firnê da çêdikir.
 
Time progressed... We made it in the oven.

468
00:24:59,000 --> 00:25:01,000
Hati bîra te wextê kehrebê hat? Tê bîra te?
 
Do you remember when electricity came? Do you remember?

469
00:25:01,000 --> 00:25:03,000
Erê... erê... belê, ev... min natê bîra min...
 
Yes... yes... yes, this... I don't remember...

470
00:25:03,000 --> 00:25:04,000
Tu bixwe... tu ji gundê Çolaqa ye lê?
 
You yourself... are you from the village of Çolaqa?

471
00:25:04,000 --> 00:25:08,000
Nê... ev bûk e ez Çeqelê Cûmê me, ev bûka Çoloqaye.
 
No... she is the bride, I am from Çeqelê Cûmê, she is the
bride of Çoloqaye.

472
00:25:08,000 --> 00:25:09,000
Çeqelê Cûmê.
 
Çeqelê Cûmê.

473
00:25:09,000 --> 00:25:10,000
Erê.
 
Yes.

474
00:25:10,000 --> 00:25:11,000
Serçava.
 
You are welcome.

475
00:25:11,000 --> 00:25:12,000
Sax bî.
 
Be healthy.

476
00:25:12,000 --> 00:25:15,000
Tê ji wî gundî ez ji te bipirsim...
 
I want to ask you about that village...

477
00:25:15,000 --> 00:25:17,000
Mêvanên we ji ku derê ne?
 
Where are your guests from?

478
00:25:17,000 --> 00:25:20,000
Ew mivana me Kobanî ye... heval.
 
Our guest is from Kobani... friend.

479
00:25:20,000 --> 00:25:21,000
Ew ji Kobanê ye?
 
Is she from Kobani?

480
00:25:21,000 --> 00:25:21,000
Ji Kobanê ye...
 
Yes.

481
00:25:21,000 --> 00:25:22,000
Ji Kobanê ye...
 
She's from Kobani...

482
00:25:22,000 --> 00:25:24,000
Ji Kobanê. Qedê... Heleca min.
 
From Kobani. My God... My problem.

483
00:25:24,000 --> 00:25:25,000
Ser çava.
 
Welcome.

484
00:25:25,000 --> 00:25:28,000
Rojekî em çûnê, em mêvan ji gundê Helebciyê em çûn.
 
One day we went, we went as guests from the village of
Halabja.

485
00:25:28,000 --> 00:25:31,000
Şikefta qîz qelha... heye li vir, em çûnê.
 
There is a girls' cave... over here, we went there.

486
00:25:31,000 --> 00:25:35,000
Ew şikefta av jinên mezin... a qedîm... aberiya...
 
That cave, big women... the ancient one... from the past...

487
00:25:35,000 --> 00:25:36,000
Erê... rojên kî me çûn.
 
Yes... the days when we went.

488
00:25:36,000 --> 00:25:37,000
Yanî asarên kevin hene...
 
So there are ancient ruins...

489
00:25:37,000 --> 00:25:38,000
Erê.
 
Yes.

490
00:25:38,000 --> 00:25:40,000
Ew asara hina wenda nebiye.
 
Those ruins have not been lost.

491
00:25:40,000 --> 00:25:41,000
Te mêvan daritî ji Efrînê...
 
Did you host guests from Afrin...

492
00:25:41,000 --> 00:25:46,000
Ez mêvandariya min... Nexêr ez li Efrînê rûniştî me. Lê ez
bi mêvandariya min hatiye... li Efrînê ez li vira dijîm...
li gundan me...
 
My hosting... No, I live in Afrin. But I came as a guest...
I live here in Afrin... in our villages...

493
00:25:46,000 --> 00:25:46,000
Ser serê sax bî.
 
You are welcome.

494
00:25:46,000 --> 00:25:48,000
Ser serê sax bî.
 
Thank you.

495
00:25:48,000 --> 00:25:51,000
Daye... we li Kobanê çi çêdikir dema cejnê de?
 
Mother... what did you make in Kobani during Eid?

496
00:25:51,000 --> 00:25:53,000
Dema Cejna da em çêdibin kulor.
 
During Eid, we make pastries.

497
00:25:53,000 --> 00:25:55,000
Li Efrînê jî dibêjên qunbe, we dibêjên kulor.
 
In Afrin they say qunbe, you say kulor.

498
00:25:55,000 --> 00:25:58,000
Em dibêjin kulor... Û meleti me cişîr jî dibêje kulûçan.
 
We call it kulor... And our neighbors also call it kuluçan.

499
00:25:58,000 --> 00:26:00,000
Dibêjin kuliçe, Her tişt hene.
 
They call it kuliche, there's everything.

500
00:26:00,000 --> 00:26:02,000
Em bi tiştêk, nemîxwas, wate ya...
 
With something, not just that, it means...

501
00:26:02,000 --> 00:26:04,000
Em çêdikirin...
 
We made...

502
00:26:04,000 --> 00:26:06,000
Berê... yanî...
 
In the past... I mean...

503
00:26:06,000 --> 00:26:09,000
...di berê de firne tinebû, keherebe tinebû...
 
...in the past there was no oven, no electricity...

504
00:26:09,000 --> 00:26:11,000
Me tenûr çêdikirin.
 
We made tandoors.

505
00:26:11,000 --> 00:26:13,000
Tenûr çêdikirin...
 
They made tandoors...

506
00:26:13,000 --> 00:26:16,000
Bikiriye me tan, me çêdikirin me dida ser.
 
We bought flour, we prepared it, and we placed it on top.

507
00:26:16,000 --> 00:26:17,000
Hevdu me dîkirên, tenûr...
 
We gathered, tandoor...

508
00:26:17,000 --> 00:26:21,000
Me aliyê xwe acêdikir. Ew arî sor dibû, dibû wextê mîrî.
 
We made our dough. The flour turned red, it was like ember
time.

509
00:26:21,000 --> 00:26:24,000
Em êca bi destan, me kulorê xwe lê dixistin.
 
Then with our hands, we placed our kulors.

510
00:26:24,000 --> 00:26:26,000
Me sor dikirin, çêdikirin me radikirin.
 
We fried them, made them, took them out.

511
00:26:26,000 --> 00:26:30,000
Fata ro kû çû, elhemdulillah keherebe hat. Bûne firne.
 
Then time passed, Alhamdulillah electricity came. There were
ovens.

512
00:26:30,000 --> 00:26:33,000
Em niha jî li firna da çêdikin, elehmedulîlah.
 
We still make them in the oven, Alhamdulillah.

513
00:26:33,000 --> 00:26:37,000
Înşela... dunyeke saxe be li serkeftinê, înşela.
 
Inshallah... may the world be healthy and victorious,
inshallah.

514
00:26:37,000 --> 00:26:40,000
Baxwe, di serokê me re , di nava de, bibîn. Bi Eydan de.
 
By ourselves, with our leader, among us, we see. In Eid.

515
00:26:40,000 --> 00:26:44,000
Înşela, li serkeftin em hemû... dunyayê erew serkeftin...
 
Inshallah, for the success of all of us... the world's
success...

516
00:26:44,000 --> 00:26:46,000
Spas dera, sax bî.
 
Thank you, stay healthy.

517
00:26:46,000 --> 00:27:06,000
Destê we sax bin.
 
May your hands be healthy.

518
00:27:13,000 --> 00:27:20,000
Şeş pakrewanên ji gundê henê: Şehîd Sîpan, Zinar Efrîn,
Bedirxan, Dogan Botan, Ferîde, Şehîd Mistefa Abdo...
 
Six martyrs from these villages: Martyr Sipan, Zinar Efrin,
Bedirxan, Dogan Botan, Feride, Martyr Mistefa Abdo...

519
00:27:20,000 --> 00:27:24,000
Komîna gund bi navê şehîd Sîpan hate binavkirin.
 
The village commune was named after Martyr Sipan.

520
00:27:24,000 --> 00:27:28,000
Hêjaya bibîrxistinê ye ku yek ji dengbêjên bi navûdeng Cemîl
Horo...
 
It is worth mentioning that one of the famous singers Cemîl
Horo...

521
00:27:28,000 --> 00:27:33,000
nêzî 30 salî li gundê Çoloqê, jiyana xwe di nava gundiyên wê
de derbas kiriye...
 
Spent nearly 30 years in the village of Çoloqê, living among
its villagers...

522
00:27:33,000 --> 00:27:36,000
û li malbateke wê gundê zewiciye.
 
and married into a family from that village.

523
00:27:36,000 --> 00:27:41,000
Ta sala 1962iyan da dimîne û pişt re koçberî bajarê Helebê
dibe.
 
He stayed until 1962 and then migrated to the city of
Aleppo.

524
00:27:41,000 --> 00:27:44,000
Jiber hemûna Xelîl Axayê gund ku weke kesayetiyek mezîn
bû...
 
Due to the presence of Khalil Agha of the village, who was a
great figure...

525
00:27:44,000 --> 00:27:47,000
û nêzî 13 gundan bi wî ve girêdayî bûn...
 
and nearly 13 villages were connected to him...

526
00:27:47,000 --> 00:27:50,000
derfet ji derketina gelek Pîşesaziyan vebû...
 
It created opportunities for many industries to emerge...

527
00:27:50,000 --> 00:28:10,000
Û gelek firoşgeh û her wekî din dervetî kar hatin vekirin.
 
And many shops and similar work opportunities were opened.

528
00:28:52,000 --> 00:28:56,000
Belê... niha em derbasî mala Xelîl Axa bûn.
 
Yes... now we have entered Khalil Agha's house.

529
00:28:56,000 --> 00:28:59,000
Me xwest hin tiştan em di derbarê Xelîl Axa jî nas bikin.
 
We wanted to learn some things about Khalil Agha too.

530
00:28:59,000 --> 00:29:02,000
Em derbasî malê bûn û malbatê de bi navê Mihemed.
 
We entered the house and with the family in the name of
Muhammad.

531
00:29:02,000 --> 00:29:04,000
Merheba serçavan...
 
Hello, you are welcome...

532
00:29:04,000 --> 00:29:07,000
Ehlensehlen... Serçavan hatine mala xwe.
 
Welcome... You have come to your home.

533
00:29:07,000 --> 00:29:12,000
Berî ku em biçin dîrokê ev hemî axa bûn.
 
Before we go into history, all of these were aghas.

534
00:29:12,000 --> 00:29:16,000
Yek jî Xelîl Axa ye. Eger em derbarê Xelîl Axa bizanibin...
 
One of them is Khalil Agha. If we want to know about Khalil
Agha...

535
00:29:16,000 --> 00:29:23,000
Dema ew derbasî Parlamentoya Sûriyê bû, ango kurteyek di
derbarê Xelîl Axa...
 
When he entered the Syrian Parliament, that is, a short
summary about Khalil Agha...

536
00:29:23,000 --> 00:29:29,000
Di destpêkê da wextê ku hukmeta Sûriyê, yanê dema derbasî...
 
In the beginning, when the Syrian government, I mean when it
entered...

537
00:29:29,000 --> 00:29:37,000
Ji binî da helbet Kutleya Wetenî bû. Şoreşa Hanano re bû
Xelîl Axa.
 
In the beginning, of course, it was the National Bloc.
Khalil Agha was with Hanano's revolution.

538
00:29:37,000 --> 00:29:41,000
Şoreşa Hanano wextê têk çû... wextê Şoreşa Hanano têk çû...
 
When the Hanano Revolution failed... when the Hanano
Revolution failed...

539
00:29:41,000 --> 00:29:47,000
Êdî dewleta Sûriyê yanê intîxaba xwen çêkirin. Hilbijartina
Meclîsa Şab çêbû.
 
Then the Syrian government created their own elections. The
parliamentary elections took place.

540
00:29:47,000 --> 00:29:55,000
Xwe berbijêr kir Xelîl Axa. Û derket Parlamantoya Sûriyê
yanê...
 
Khalil Agha nominated himself. And entered the Syrian
Parliament, that is...

541
00:29:55,000 --> 00:29:57,000
Çend sale ew têda ma?
 
How many years did he stay there?

542
00:29:57,000 --> 00:30:00,000
Tê de dû-sê dewreyan ma...
 
He stayed for two or three terms...

543
00:30:00,000 --> 00:30:00,000
Sê dewran...
 
...about 10 years.

544
00:30:00,000 --> 00:30:02,000
Sê dewran...
 
Three eras...

545
00:30:02,000 --> 00:30:04,000
Rojên wan te dîtin?
 
Did you see those three eras?

546
00:30:04,000 --> 00:30:05,000
Hmm. Sê dewra.
 
Hmm. Three eras.

547
00:30:05,000 --> 00:30:06,000
Sê dewra, te dîtin ma.
 
Did I see the three eras? Yes.

548
00:30:06,000 --> 00:30:09,000
Ên destpêkê, şerê Fransa jê kirin?
 
In the beginning, were they fought by France?

549
00:30:09,000 --> 00:30:15,000
Şerê Fransa? Na, şerê Fransa jê kirin.
 
Fought by France? No, they fought France.

550
00:30:15,000 --> 00:30:21,000
Bi sêwre ra, pir hereke... Çekên sêwre yên, wacî mantiqa
şimalî dibên.
 
With the revolution, there was a lot of movement... The
weapons of the revolution that faced the northern region,
they say.

551
00:30:21,000 --> 00:30:26,000
Wacî Helebê, vir da, cîh kirin mêrên ciwanan wilo.
 
Facing Aleppo, here, they placed young men like that.

552
00:30:26,000 --> 00:30:30,000
Jê Tirkiyê jî kîsî xwe teb'en, ew kirrîn, sîleh kirrîn.
 
From Turkey as well, from their own pocket, of course, they
bought them, they bought weapons.

553
00:30:30,000 --> 00:30:37,000
Û wekîlê xwe hebû, Îbrahîmê Tirgo d'gotin, ji gundê Çeqela.
 
And they had a deputy, Ibrahim Tirgo, they called him, from
the village of Chaqala.

554
00:30:37,000 --> 00:30:41,000
Derbasî berlamanê Sûriyê bû.
 
He entered the parliament of Syria.

555
00:30:41,000 --> 00:30:45,000
Û heta da çû karê xwe yê berlemanê dikir.
 
And he went back and forth doing his parliament work.

556
00:30:45,000 --> 00:30:49,000
Pir tişt heye, ji Kurda xêr ra qedimandin.
 
There are many things he provided for the benefit of the
Kurds.

557
00:30:49,000 --> 00:30:54,000
Qedimandin, wekî mesela
 
They provided, for example,

558
00:30:54,000 --> 00:30:56,000
Luẍetê Kurmancî da pêş.
 
He presented the Kurmanji language.

559
00:30:56,000 --> 00:30:59,000
Înna luẍetek Kurdî.
 
So there is a Kurdish language.

560
00:30:59,000 --> 00:31:05,000
Bi zimanê xwe em l'vê derê b'elim in, bixwînin.
 
That we learn in our language here, that we read it.

561
00:31:05,000 --> 00:31:12,000
Û wî çaxî jî te zanî her teqrîben her şeş meha, sê meha, şeş
meha reîsek dihat.
 
And in that time, you know, almost every six months, three
months, six months, a president would come.

562
00:31:12,000 --> 00:31:15,000
Yanî reîsek in, înqilabat pir lê çêdibûn wî çaxan a.
 
Meaning a president, there were a lot of coups at that time.

563
00:31:15,000 --> 00:31:20,000
Ê kîjan reîs e ewê demê bi Xelîl Axa ra derbazî gotinê wî
bû?
 
Which president was it at that time who had that
conversation with Khalil Agha?

564
00:31:20,000 --> 00:31:23,000
Şukrî Quwetlî.
 
Shukri al-Quwatli.

565
00:31:23,000 --> 00:31:27,000
Ev o Şukrî Quwetlî hat Efrînê, û Çolaqê.
 
This Shukri al-Quwatli, he came to Afrin and Cholaqa.

566
00:31:27,000 --> 00:31:31,000
Bes, bi çûyînê hat Efrînê û Çolaqê.
 
Yes, by going, he came to Afrin and Cholaqa.

567
00:31:31,000 --> 00:31:37,000
Evna, wextê, îctîma'ê xwe yê perlemanê, l' Şamê, perlemanê
rûdiniştin.
 
These, during the time of their parliament meetings, in
Damascus, they would sit in the parliament.

568
00:31:37,000 --> 00:31:42,000
Ba'dê îctîma'ê xwe, xilas dibin, evna diçûn, mektebê reîsê
cumhûrî rûdiniştin.
 
After their meeting was finished, they would go and sit in
the president's office.

569
00:31:42,000 --> 00:31:46,000
Naîb diçûn, mektebê rûdiniştin.
 
The deputies would go and sit in the office.

570
00:31:46,000 --> 00:31:52,000
Ê, reîs cumhurî, mesxereyek bi Xelîl Axa ra kir.
 
Well, the president joked with Khalil Agha.

571
00:31:52,000 --> 00:31:57,000
Gotê, Xelîl Axa, gotê Zabadanî carê din...
 
He said to him, Khalil Agha, he said Zabadani another
time...

572
00:31:57,000 --> 00:32:05,000
Xelîl Axa go "Na, min caran nedî ye", ha bi taybetî Xelîl
axa jî timî l' mesyafê diçû wê derê mesyafê yanî.
 
Khalil Agha said: "No, I haven't seen it." - especially
Khalil Agha was always going to the resorts there, to the
resort.

573
00:32:05,000 --> 00:32:11,000
Go "Na min nedî ye Zabadanî." Ê go "te tişt dinê da nedî ye!
Heyatê xwe te tişt nedî ye!"
 
He said: "No, I haven't seen Zabadani." The president said:
"You haven't seen anything else! You haven't seen anything
in your life!"

574
00:32:11,000 --> 00:32:14,000
Go "Te Blûdan dî ye?" Go "Na weleh", ê go "te tişt nedî ye!"
 
He said: "Have you seen Bludan?" He said: "No, by God." He
said: "You haven't seen anything!"

575
00:32:14,000 --> 00:32:15,000
Destê xwe ha ra kir,
 
He raised his hand like this.

576
00:32:15,000 --> 00:32:18,000
Go: "Sual! Siyadet el-Reîs!"
 
He said: "A question! Mr. President!"

577
00:32:18,000 --> 00:32:19,000
Got: "Kerem be."
 
He said: "Go ahead."

578
00:32:19,000 --> 00:32:22,000
Go: "Siyadet el-Reîs, te Çolaqê dî ye?"
 
He said: "Mr. President, have you seen Cholaqa?"

579
00:32:22,000 --> 00:32:24,000
Go: "Na weleh, min nedî ye."
 
He said: "No, by God, I haven't seen it."

580
00:32:24,000 --> 00:32:35,000
Ê go: "Te jî tiştek nedî ye! Te gundê Feqîra dî ye?" Go "Na
weleh." Go "te Gewrika dî ye?" "Na weleh." Go "evna gundên
kî ne?"
 
Well, he said: "You also, you also haven't seen anything!
Have you seen the village of Faqiran?" He said "No, by God."
He said "Have you seen Gawrika?" "No, by God." He said
"Whose villages are these?"

581
00:32:35,000 --> 00:32:38,000
Go: "Evna gundên min in!
 
He said: "These are my villages!"

582
00:32:38,000 --> 00:32:40,000
"Gundê têda, min in."
 
"The villages we stayed in."

583
00:32:40,000 --> 00:32:46,000
Ê, go "wellahî gava vê carê ez werim muhafezetê Helebê, go
ez ê werim cem te Efrînê û Çolaqê."
 
Well, he said: "By God, when I come to the Aleppo
governorate this time, I will come to you, to Afrin and
Cholaqa."

584
00:32:46,000 --> 00:32:49,000
Û fi'len hat Efrînê û Çolaqê.
 
And indeed he came to Afrin and Cholaqa.

585
00:32:49,000 --> 00:32:57,000
Efrîn jî bi saya Xelîl Axa bû. Û tê de qismek cîranê me jî
hebûn.
 
Afrin was also thanks to Khalil Agha. And a part of our
neighbors were also there.

586
00:32:57,000 --> 00:33:00,000
Berî Xelîl Axa, bavê wî hebû, Mihemed? Evo?
 
Before Khalil Agha, was his father there, Mihemed? Is that
him?

587
00:33:00,000 --> 00:33:06,000
Bavê xwe, Mihemed Axayê Seydo Mêmo digotin. Nav lê kirin Axa
Mezin.
 
His father, they called him Mihemed Agha of Seydo Memo. They
named him the Great Agha.

588
00:33:06,000 --> 00:33:14,000
Heta ku axaleran nav hev de, ji heft biran ra, axayê mezin
li heftê danîn yanî.
 
Even among the Aghas, among the seven brothers, they placed
him as the Great Agha of the seven.

589
00:33:14,000 --> 00:33:22,000
Zemanê.. sêwra Şêx Seîd de, axayê mezin muşareke kir, yanî
Mihemed Axayê Seydo Mêmo muşareke kir.
 
During the time of... Sheikh Said's revolution, the Great
Agha participated, meaning Mihemed Agha of Seydo Memo
participated.

590
00:33:22,000 --> 00:33:27,000
Û eynî l' wê malê wefdê Şêx Seîd hatin l' wê derê.
 
And in that exact same house, the delegation of Sheikh Said
came there.

591
00:33:27,000 --> 00:33:32,000
Ma'ne, sêwrê... evê wê kî çêkin.
 
Meaning, the revolution... they were going to start it.

592
00:33:32,000 --> 00:33:41,000
Xeber şand, Şêx Seîd ji kalê min re got, ma'ne bi me re
hareke.
 
They sent word, Sheikh Said told my grandfather, meaning
'make a move with us.'

593
00:33:41,000 --> 00:33:50,000
Kalê min tab'an fawren cab da, got 'em hazir in, bi malê
xwe, bi canê xwe, bi gî...'
 
My grandfather, of course, replied immediately, he said 'we
are ready, with our wealth, with our souls, with our
lives...'

594
00:33:50,000 --> 00:33:54,000
'Em ji kurdistanê xwe re em hazir in'.
 
'We are ready for our Kurdistan.'

595
00:33:54,000 --> 00:34:00,000
Û ji axalerên din re jî şandin. Êlçî çûn axalerên din jî.
 
And they also sent to the other Aghas. The messengers went
to the other Aghas too.

596
00:34:00,000 --> 00:34:05,000
Bes e muhîme, ev axayê mezin l'wê derê yekî go 'bajar gî
çêkin'.
 
But the important thing is, this great Agha there, someone
said 'let's build a small city.'

597
00:34:05,000 --> 00:34:09,000
'Bajar gî çêkin, ba go, nexwe weke ser avê da bajar gî
çêkin.'
 
'Let's build a small city.' Then he said, 'well, go build a
small city on the water.'

598
00:34:09,000 --> 00:34:12,000
Van e wa bajarê Efrînê çêkir.
 
So they built the city of Afrin.

599
00:34:12,000 --> 00:34:19,000
Mihemed axayê Seydo Mêmo destpêkir, ji wir da, ji vir da
destpê bû yane.
 
Mihemed Agha of Seydo Memo started it, from there, from here
it started.

600
00:34:19,000 --> 00:34:28,000
Ew dem e, Efrîn çi bû? Firansa... tişt... qereqola, ev
şaredarî, ew mehkeme, ew wan Firansa çêkir?
 
At that time, what was Afrin? The French... things... police
stations, this municipality, that court, did France build
those?

601
00:34:28,000 --> 00:34:34,000
Ê gundê Efrîn bi xwe ma hebû? Tê de, tab'an, destpê kirin bi
înşaatê.
 
Well, was the village of Afrin itself there? In it, of
course, they started with construction.

602
00:34:34,000 --> 00:34:38,000
Sarayê, û qesrê xwe girt, Xelîl axa.
 
Khalil Agha took the palace and his mansion.

603
00:34:38,000 --> 00:34:41,000
Û hebs û otêl û xan çêkirin.
 
And he built a prison, a hotel, and a inn.

604
00:34:41,000 --> 00:34:47,000
Ev tişt ha gişt çêkirin, teberru' bi hikûmetê kirin paşê.
 
They built all these things, then they donated them to the
government later.

605
00:34:47,000 --> 00:34:53,000
Bi xwa, tenzîmê Efrîn, mûxettet, ji Fransa ji wan hat,
mûxettet.
 
Actually, the planning of Afrin, the blueprint, it came from
France, the blueprint.

606
00:34:53,000 --> 00:35:01,000
Nefs mûxettetê Barîs e yanî. Hawa kolanê wê dîtî.. înna wekî
Parîs e.. evî Efrîn mûxettet in.
 
It's the same blueprint as Paris. When you see its
streets... so it's like Paris... they planned this Afrin.

607
00:35:01,000 --> 00:35:11,000
Înna wekî şatrenc... çêbibe... ma'neya wê ew e yê... tîrêja
rojê sihhîyen bi kî derê da tê.
 
That it be like a chessboard... its meaning is that... the
sun rays come in a healthy way everywhere.

608
00:35:11,000 --> 00:35:15,000
Îman gir ew ki kuna... rojkê.. d'giş derê de tê.
 
Believe me, every hole... the sun... reaches everywhere.

609
00:35:15,000 --> 00:35:18,000
Gelek sihiyyan... tibbiyyan yanî.
 
Very healthy... medically speaking.

610
00:35:18,000 --> 00:35:20,000
Mala te ava be, sipas ji te re.
 
May your house be prosperous, thank you.

611
00:35:20,000 --> 00:35:40,000
Te re jî sipas. Ehlen û sehlen, ser çavên me... hatin we re
jî ...em şa bûn, lagî we jî...
 
Thank you too. Welcome, upon our eyes... we are glad you
came... to us too...

612
00:36:00,000 --> 00:36:03,000
Bijîjkekî binavê, Enwer.
 
A doctor named Enwer.

613
00:36:03,000 --> 00:36:07,000
Di sala hezar û nehsed û pêncî û dudiyan de...
 
From the year nineteen fifty-two...

614
00:36:07,000 --> 00:36:10,000
Ta sala hezar û nehsed û pêncî û heftan...
 
Until the year nineteen fifty-seven...

615
00:36:10,000 --> 00:36:11,000
Li gund bijîşkek hek fakîr.
 
There was like a poor doctor in the village.

616
00:36:11,000 --> 00:36:14,000
Û li gundan ji bo dermankirina nexweşiyan digeriya.
 
And he wandered the villages to treat illnesses.

617
00:36:14,000 --> 00:36:16,000
Piştre barkir çû Helebê.
 
Then he moved to Aleppo.

618
00:36:16,000 --> 00:36:19,000
Kesekî bi navê Îbikê Omkêlê,
 
Someone named Ibik of Omkêlê,

619
00:36:19,000 --> 00:36:21,000
Tevî çend hevalên xwe di dema...
 
Along with a few of his friends, during...

620
00:36:21,000 --> 00:36:23,000
Serweriya Fransizan da, li ser Sûriyê da,
 
The French rule over Syria,

621
00:36:23,000 --> 00:36:25,000
Diçûn gundê Hemamê...
 
They went to the village of Hamam...

622
00:36:25,000 --> 00:36:28,000
Şer û berxwedanî, li dijî, dagirkeriya Fransizan dikirin.
 
And they fought and resisted against the French occupation.

623
00:36:28,000 --> 00:36:47,000
Û piştre vedigeriyan gundê xwe.
 
And then they would return to their village.

624
00:36:47,000 --> 00:37:01,000
Nnnamo dilê min yara kekê dilê min yara dilê min yara qumetê
dilê min yara...
 
Oh my heart, oh brother, my heart...

625
00:37:01,000 --> 00:37:08,000
Xwedê te nehêle qîzika perîyan e e...
 
May God not spare you, you jealous one, fairy girl...

626
00:37:08,000 --> 00:37:11,000
L'xelkê re pûstek al' Efrînê, kêşa yî...
 
You have brought hardship upon the people of Afrin...

627
00:37:11,000 --> 00:37:13,000
Xwedê ev zalimê re, heftan e e e...
 
God to these tyrants...

628
00:37:13,000 --> 00:37:16,000
Şeva av li me... li me vê şevê...
 
Night and water surround us this night...

629
00:37:16,000 --> 00:37:19,000
Xweberdan e, ser bajarê Cezîra Botana e e e...
 
They descended upon the city of Cizira Botan...

630
00:37:19,000 --> 00:37:22,000
Ketim davê qesr û qonaxê wî tan e e e...
 
I fell into the trap of that palace and its courtyards...

631
00:37:22,000 --> 00:37:25,000
Ji meqamê e, dilbera rebena te dan e,
 
From the place of the poor beloved, they have given you...

632
00:37:25,000 --> 00:37:29,000
Lo welo, welo, welo, lo welo, welo welo welo.
 
Oh alas, alas, alas...

633
00:37:29,000 --> 00:37:49,000
Ha wer, siltan e Kurdistan hat l'me te wa e e e... welo.
 
Come, the Sultan of Kurdistan has come to us... alas.

634
00:37:58,000 --> 00:38:11,000
Nnamo, dilê min wa e e, kekê dilê min wa e e, dilê min wa e
e, qumetê dilê min wa a a a.
 
Oh my heart, oh brother, my heart...

635
00:38:11,000 --> 00:38:14,000
Erê dilê min e, kul e, kul e a girtî jan e...
 
Yes my heart is full of sorrow, a hidden pain...

636
00:38:14,000 --> 00:38:21,000
Ta marê çola bi sar û ... kêçika milê da şaxê berdan e...
 
Even the snake of the desert and the cold have thrown their
branches upon our shoulders...

637
00:38:21,000 --> 00:38:23,000
Ez rê me şev da qe qula û derdan e...
 
I am on the road in the night of holes and pain...

638
00:38:23,000 --> 00:38:26,000
M' j' wî warî xwe dît e, kul û birîn ê, Xwedê ye berqa û
doxan e e e...
 
I have seen the pain and wounds from my own homeland, by
God's lightning and smoke...

639
00:38:26,000 --> 00:38:31,000
Şeva tekamila min a bê namil e l' çû derman e...
 
My perfect night is without hope, there is no medicine...

640
00:38:31,000 --> 00:38:36,000
De welo, welo welo welo, de welo welo welo welo...
 
Oh alas, alas, alas...

641
00:38:36,000 --> 00:38:44,000
Bavê Cemîl hat... m' t'welo... welo welo welo...
 
Father of Cemil has come... alas, alas...

642
00:38:44,000 --> 00:38:49,000
Şevê te re şîne, nexweşikê lo o o...
 
The night is blue for you, oh beautiful one...

643
00:38:49,000 --> 00:38:54,000
Rûkê te sor in, wek pelê gulan e e...
 
Your cheeks are red, like the petals of roses...

644
00:38:54,000 --> 00:39:03,000
Şevê te re şîn e, nexweşikê lo o o... rûkê te sor e, e...
 
The night is blue for you, oh beautiful one...

645
00:39:03,000 --> 00:39:08,000
Wek pela gul e e.
 
Like the petals of a rose...

646
00:39:08,000 --> 00:39:12,000
Zîndar e, çavê te e...
 
Your eyes are alive...

647
00:39:12,000 --> 00:39:19,000
Canê min te heland, canê min te heland, canê min te
haland...
 
You have melted my soul, melted my soul...

648
00:39:19,000 --> 00:39:32,000
Zîndar e çavê te e e e... canê min heland, canê min heland,
canê min heland...
 
Your eyes are alive... You have melted my soul, melted my
soul...

649
00:39:32,000 --> 00:39:34,000
Belê temaşevanên hêja,
 
Yes, esteemed viewers,

650
00:39:34,000 --> 00:39:36,000
Îro em l'gundê Çolaqan in.
 
Today we are in the village of Cholaqan.

651
00:39:36,000 --> 00:39:42,000
Me xwest, hinekî ji jiyana dengbêjê me ê nemir, Cemîl
Horo... em pêşkêşî we bikin.
 
We wanted to present to you a bit from the life of our
immortal Dengbej, Cemil Horo.

652
00:39:42,000 --> 00:39:45,000
Em derbazî, cem malbata wî bûn. Malbata wî li vir e.
 
We have come to his family. His family is here.

653
00:39:45,000 --> 00:39:51,000
Hizar rehmet l' gora dengbêjê nemir Cemîl Horo û hemî
şehîdên me yê Kurda be.
 
A thousand mercies on the grave of the immortal Dengbej
Cemil Horo and all our Kurdish martyrs.

654
00:39:51,000 --> 00:39:56,000
Di rojên cejnê da em derbaz bûn, me xwest em malbata wî jî
nas bikin.
 
We visited during the days of Eid, we wanted to get to know
his family as well.

655
00:39:56,000 --> 00:39:57,000
Merheba ji we re.
 
Hello to you.

656
00:39:57,000 --> 00:40:00,000
Ehlen wa sehlen, b'xêr hatin..
 
Welcome, you are welcome...

657
00:40:00,000 --> 00:40:18,000
...Erê. Xwedê ez û... ehbabekî min, Doktor Ozod, ew ji hindê
vî alî ma, em di gund de ne. Min go bernameya we xêr û welat
hatiye, me go înşaellah wekî em karin em îstiqbal kin bi
çavê xwe û bi dilê xwe.
 
...Yes. By God, me and a friend of mine, Doctor Ozod, I have
reached these places, I am a villager. I said your program
has arrived, God willing, as much as we can, we will welcome
it with our eyes and our hearts.

658
00:40:18,000 --> 00:40:34,000
Kek Dîro, te di çend perçeyên Kurdistanê, Cemîl Horo hat
naskirin, û pir dengbêjên xelkê stranê wî gotin. Em dest pê
bikin, em dixwazin malbata wî nas bikin.
 
Brother Diro, in how many parts of Kurdistan was Cemil Horo
known, and many local dengbêjs sang his songs. Let's start,
we want to know his family.

659
00:40:34,000 --> 00:40:36,000
Henîfe çend bira ne, çend xwîşk in?
 
How many brothers and sisters does Hanîfe have?

660
00:40:36,000 --> 00:40:52,000
Em pênc bira ne, yê mezin Piling. Da wî nas kirin bi navê vî
Piling. Navê wî Ehmed bû. Rehmetî bû... Em çar mane di navna
de. Dîkan min xwîşka xwe ye. Xwedê siheta we xweş ke.
 
We are five brothers, the oldest is Piling. They knew him by
the name of Piling. His name was Ahmed. He passed away...
The four of us are left. The rest are my sisters. May God
give you good health.

661
00:40:52,000 --> 00:40:56,000
Kê dest bi vî karî kir?
 
Who started this work?

662
00:40:56,000 --> 00:41:08,000
Xwedê Elî heye birayê minî biçûk, û Ehmed heye xwedê wî
beyle... eh, ha zor agahî ye beyle. Ew ji biçûkî dest bi
karikî rakiribû.
 
By God, there is Ali, my younger brother, and there is
Ahmed, God... uh, he was very knowledgeable. He started
working from a young age.

663
00:41:08,000 --> 00:41:09,000
Tu jî stran nabêjî?
 
Do you not sing as well?

664
00:41:09,000 --> 00:41:14,000
Xwedê ez dibêjim. Lê em bi dengê Ehmed jî yê xweştir e.
 
By God, I do. But Ahmed's voice is better than mine.

665
00:41:14,000 --> 00:41:20,000
Em dixwazin, te zanîbû, me dixwast Cemîl Horo nas xweş ba em
bidîta.
 
We wish, you know, we wished Cemil Horo was alive and we
could see him.

666
00:41:20,000 --> 00:41:23,000
Emrî xwedê ye.
 
It is God's will.

667
00:41:23,000 --> 00:41:31,000
Ew dengbêjê ku me... bi rastî bê miraz di navna barkirin. Te
temî bang dikirin azadî û bang dikirin Kurdistan.
 
That dengbêj that we... truly passed away without achieving
his goals. He always called for freedom and called for
Kurdistan.

668
00:41:31,000 --> 00:41:38,000
Baxê wî lê bi hesret çûn. Û neçarî jî dikir, zane.
 
He passed away with longing. And he was helpless, you know.

669
00:41:38,000 --> 00:41:46,000
E, pir cefa dît. Yanî li vir, li wa, hikûmeta... li vir pir
hatin girtin, van û dîke de girtin...
 
Yes, he suffered a lot. I mean here, there, the
government... he was arrested here many times, they arrested
him again...

670
00:41:46,000 --> 00:41:54,000
Dewleta Sûriyê. Erê, di Sûriyê jî, û li Tirka jî, dema
stranê Şêx Seîd, li wir jî em surgun bûn.
 
The Syrian government. Yes, in Syria too, and in Turkey too,
during the song of Sheikh Said, we were exiled there too.

671
00:41:54,000 --> 00:42:01,000
Yanî pir geriyaye li Kurdistanê? Başûr, û nêzîk... Li Bakur
û Başûr û Rojava, rojeke ava bû?
 
I mean, has he traveled a lot in Kurdistan? The South, and
close... In the North, South, and West, did he ever settle
down for a day?

672
00:42:01,000 --> 00:42:04,000
Belê. Ez am, demekî ku Cizîrê rûniştî bûm...
 
Yes. When I lived in Cizire for a while...

673
00:42:04,000 --> 00:42:22,000
Demek xwestek wî li dinyayê hebû. Digot 'ya rebî ma
Kurdistan ava bibûya.' ... 'ez dixwazim ez di vî ser tirbeyê
min...' ... 'ez bê bab û reb li Kurdistan ava bibûya, ez pê
bihesim.' Lê ew bi hesreta xwe ya axînê pê ve çû.
 
He had a wish in the world for a while. He used to say, 'Oh
Lord, if only Kurdistan were built.' ... 'I want to be on my
grave...' ... 'I would feel it even if I were without a
father and Lord, if Kurdistan were built.' But he passed
away with his sighing longing.

674
00:42:22,000 --> 00:42:30,000
Ew Neşet Ertaş heye, ... ew jî dengbêjek Tirkan e, bi nav û
deng e... ew jî berî vî rehmetî bû.
 
There is Neşet Ertaş... he is also a Turkish dengbêj,
famous... he also passed away before him.

675
00:42:30,000 --> 00:42:32,000
Piştî rehmetî bû.
 
He passed away after him.

676
00:42:32,000 --> 00:42:41,000
Piştî rehmetî bû. Hemî televîzyonên Tirkan, rojnamevanên
Tirkan behs dikirin, digotin Neşet Ertaş stranên Cemîl Horo
dibêje.
 
He passed away after him. All Turkish televisions, Turkish
journalists were talking, they were saying Neşet Ertaş sings
Cemil Horo's songs.

677
00:42:41,000 --> 00:42:51,000
Bi xwedê birêz ez nagihiştime wan tiştan, lê hema
tenbûrvanekî ku ji vira ji Kurda re... Wahîd, Wahîd Xelîl li
wir radihiştin, je nas zane.
 
By God, sir, I could not reach those things, but there was a
tambura player from here for the Kurds... Wahid, they used
to bring Wahid Xelil there, he knew him.

678
00:42:51,000 --> 00:43:00,000
Ew dibû wesîlete bera qêy wî bavê min, û ji Neşed ra, çunkî
ewe ku nav bavê min... ewe ku dixwaze xweşiya xwe nîşan
bide, ... dixwaze şirîtek ji xwe ra bîne. Digot "ez dixwazim
tu şirîtan xwedê jî rahêlî."
 
He became a means for my father, and for Neşed, because he
knew my father's name... he who wants to show his
goodness... wants to bring a tape for himself. He said, "I
want you to bring the tapes too, for God's sake."

679
00:43:00,000 --> 00:43:08,000
Û diz dikirin, dixwaze şirîta dibe, ew ê li ser wî... dibê
wî tiştek ji min ra bîne ew...
 
And they used to steal, he wanted the tape, the one about
him... he said to bring me something from him...

680
00:43:08,000 --> 00:43:17,000
E, ser vî, Tirka hemî behs dikirin, digotin, gellek... evanê
ku rojnamevan jî hene... wan jî di gotin yane.
 
Yes, about this, the Turks all talked, they said, a lot...
those who are journalists too... they also said it, I mean.

681
00:43:17,000 --> 00:43:37,000
Televîzyonên Tirkan û rojnamevanên Tirkan hemî behs dikir,
Neşet Ertaş stranên Cemîl Horo dibêje, bes mixabin...
ragihandina Kurda tune bû yane... ew tiştên dengbêjên me
dikirin ... ba te ser vê tiştî zanîbû, nizanîbû?
 
Turkish televisions and Turkish journalists all talked,
saying Neşet Ertaş sings Cemil Horo's songs, but
unfortunately... there was no Kurdish media, I mean... those
things our dengbêjs did... did you know about this thing or
not?

682
00:43:41,000 --> 00:43:44,000
Bi xwedê ez nizanim ez negihiştim van tiştan.
 
By God, I don't know, I didn't reach these things.

683
00:43:44,000 --> 00:43:55,000
Belê temaşevanan hêca, li vir jî em ê xatirê xwe ji we
bixwazin. Li vir jî em gihiştin dawiya bernameya xwe. Îro em
li gundê Çolaqa bûn. Me bi hev re gundê Çolaqa nas kir.
 
Yes, esteemed viewers, here we will say goodbye to you. Here
we have reached the end of our program. Today we were in the
village of Cholaqa. Together we got to know the village of
Cholaqa.

684
00:43:55,000 --> 00:43:59,000
Heta hefteyekî din, em ê dîsa bi hev re bin, di bernameyekî
me ya...
 
Until another week, we will be together again, in a program
of ours...

685
00:43:59,000 --> 00:44:08,000
Ax dilê min yane... dilê min yane, dilê min yane... dilê min
yane...
 
Oh, my heart aches... my heart aches, my heart aches... my
heart aches...

686
00:44:08,000 --> 00:44:16,000
Kekê dilê min yane... xwedê dînê, malo.. hefsî qîz kirin,
pîryan e...
 
Brother, my heart aches... God's crazy one, home... they
made girls prisoners, the old ones...

687
00:44:16,000 --> 00:44:22,000
...Lê xwedê kirin, baskên kewa... firyan e. Dişiqat e ez
mînim heyran e...
 
...But God did it, the wings of partridges... flew. It's
torn, I remain amazed...

688
00:44:22,000 --> 00:44:26,000
Şeva me qamo... niştim şeva xwe... dîsa jar e... ez jê re...
botane...
 
Our night is a calamity... I sat in my night... it is poor
again... I am for her... from Botan...

689
00:44:26,000 --> 00:44:31,000
Xwedê te da vî qesra û rengê, birca belek wê li me... xwe
dane...
 
God put you in this colorful palace, its spotted tower...
submitted to us...

690
00:44:31,000 --> 00:44:35,000
Ciwamo, dilber o, reben o, zîn o, zêdan e...
 
